var book = {
	"name": "1 Chronicles",
	"numChapters": 29,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10254A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10254A\"></sup>Adam, Seth, Enosh,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Kenan, Mahalalel, Jared,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Enoch, Methuselah, Lamech,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Noah, Shem, Ham and Japheth.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10258B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10258B\"></sup>The sons of Japheth <i>were</i> Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal, Meshech and Tiras.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The sons of Gomer <i>were</i> Ashkenaz, Diphath, and Togarmah.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The sons of Javan <i>were</i> Elishah, Tarshish, Kittim and Rodanim.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The sons of Ham <i>were</i> Cush, Mizraim, Put, and Canaan.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The sons of Cush <i>were</i> Seba, Havilah, Sabta, Raama and Sabteca; and the sons of Raamah <i>were</i> Sheba and Dedan.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Cush became the father of Nimrod; he began to be a mighty one in the earth.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10264C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10264C\"></sup>Mizraim became the father of the people of Lud, Anam, Lehab, Naphtuh,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Pathrus, Casluh, from which the Philistines came, and Caphtor.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Canaan became the father of Sidon, his firstborn, Heth,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and the Jebusites, the Amorites, the Girgashites,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>the Hivites, the Arkites, the Sinites,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the Arvadites, the Zemarites and the Hamathites.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10270D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10270D\"></sup>The sons of Shem <i>were</i> Elam, Asshur, Arpachshad, Lud, Aram, Uz, Hul, Gether and Meshech.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Arpachshad became the father of Shelah and Shelah became the father of Eber.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Two sons were born to Eber, the name of the one was Peleg, for in his days the earth was divided, and his brother’s name was Joktan.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Joktan became the father of Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Ebal, Abimael, Sheba,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Ophir, Havilah and Jobab; all these <i>were</i> the sons of Joktan.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10277E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10277E\"></sup>Shem, Arpachshad, Shelah,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Eber, Peleg, Reu,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Serug, Nahor, Terah,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Abram, that is Abraham.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The sons of Abraham <i>were</i> Isaac and Ishmael.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10282F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10282F\"></sup>These are their genealogies: the firstborn of Ishmael <i>was</i> Nebaioth, then Kedar, Adbeel, Mibsam,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Mishma, Dumah, Massa, Hadad, Tema,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Jetur, Naphish and Kedemah; these <i>were</i> the sons of Ishmael.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10285G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10285G\"></sup>The sons of Keturah, Abraham’s concubine, <i>whom</i> she bore, <i>were</i> Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak and Shuah. And the sons of Jokshan <i>were</i> Sheba and Dedan.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The sons of Midian were Ephah, Epher, Hanoch, Abida and Eldaah. All these were the sons of Keturah.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10287H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10287H\"></sup>Abraham became the father of Isaac. The sons of Isaac <i>were</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10287I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10287I\"></sup>Esau and Israel.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10288J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10288J\"></sup>The sons of Esau <i>were</i> Eliphaz, Reuel, Jeush, Jalam and Korah.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>The sons of Eliphaz <i>were</i> Teman, Omar, Zephi, Gatam, Kenaz, Timna and Amalek.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>The sons of Reuel <i>were</i> Nahath, Zerah, Shammah and Mizzah.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10291K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10291K\"></sup>The sons of Seir <i>were</i> Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah, Dishon, Ezer and Dishan.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>The sons of Lotan <i>were</i> Hori and Homam; and Lotan’s sister <i>was</i> Timna.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The sons of Shobal <i>were</i> Alian, Manahath, Ebal, Shephi and Onam. And the sons of Zibeon <i>were</i> Aiah and Anah.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>The son of Anah <i>was</i> Dishon. And the sons of Dishon <i>were</i> Hamran, Eshban, Ithran and Cheran.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>The sons of Ezer <i>were</i> Bilhan, Zaavan and Jaakan. The sons of Dishan <i>were</i> Uz and Aran.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10296L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10296L\"></sup>Now these are the kings who reigned in the land of Edom before any king of the sons of Israel reigned. Bela was the son of Beor, and the name of his city was Dinhabah.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>When Bela died, Jobab the son of Zerah of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10297M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10297M\"></sup>Bozrah became king in his place.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>When Jobab died, Husham of the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10298N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10298N\"></sup>the Temanites became king in his place.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>When Husham died, Hadad the son of Bedad, who defeated Midian in the field of Moab, became king in his place; and the name of his city <i>was</i> Avith.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>When Hadad died, Samlah of Masrekah became king in his place.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>When Samlah died, Shaul of Rehoboth by the River became king in his place.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>When Shaul died, Baal-hanan the son of Achbor became king in his place.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>When Baal-hanan died, Hadad became king in his place; and the name of his city was Pai, and his wife’s name was Mehetabel, the daughter of Matred, the daughter of Mezahab.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Then Hadad died.Now the chiefs of Edom were: chief Timna, chief Aliah, chief Jetheth,",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>chief Oholibamah, chief Elah, chief Pinon,",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>chief Kenaz, chief Teman, chief Mibzar,",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>chief Magdiel, chief Iram. These <i>were</i> the chiefs of Edom."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10308A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10308A\"></sup>These are the sons of Israel: Reuben, Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, Zebulun,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Dan, Joseph, Benjamin, Naphtali, Gad and Asher.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10310B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10310B\"></sup>The sons of Judah <i>were</i> Er, Onan and Shelah; <i>these</i> three were born to him by Bath-shua the Canaanitess. And Er, Judah’s firstborn, was wicked in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, so He put him to death.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10311C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10311C\"></sup>Tamar his daughter-in-law bore him Perez and Zerah. Judah had five sons in all.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The sons of Perez <i>were</i> Hezron and Hamul.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The sons of Zerah <i>were</i> Zimri, Ethan, Heman, Calcol and Dara; five of them in all.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The son of Carmi <i>was</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10314D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10314D\"></sup>Achar, the troubler of Israel, who violated the ban.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The son of Ethan <i>was</i> Azariah.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now the sons of Hezron, who were born to him <i>were</i> Jerahmeel, Ram and Chelubai.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Ram became the father of Amminadab, and Amminadab became the father of Nahshon, leader of the sons of Judah;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Nahshon became the father of Salma, Salma became the father of Boaz,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Boaz became the father of Obed, and Obed became the father of Jesse;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and Jesse became the father of Eliab his firstborn, then Abinadab the second, Shimea the third,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Nethanel the fourth, Raddai the fifth,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Ozem the sixth, David the seventh;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and their sisters <i>were</i> Zeruiah and Abigail. And the three sons of Zeruiah <i>were</i> Abshai, Joab and Asahel.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Abigail bore Amasa, and the father of Amasa was Jether the Ishmaelite.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now Caleb the son of Hezron had sons by Azubah <i>his</i> wife, and by Jerioth; and these were her sons: Jesher, Shobab, and Ardon.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When Azubah died, Caleb married Ephrath, who bore him Hur.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Hur became the father of Uri, and Uri became the father of Bezalel.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Afterward Hezron went in to the daughter of Machir the father of Gilead, whom he married when he was sixty years old; and she bore him Segub.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Segub became the father of Jair, who had twenty-three cities in the land of Gilead.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But Geshur and Aram took the towns of Jair from them, with Kenath and its villages, <i>even</i> sixty cities. All these were the sons of Machir, the father of Gilead.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>After the death of Hezron in Caleb-ephrathah, Abijah, Hezron’s wife, bore him Ashhur the father of Tekoa.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now the sons of Jerahmeel the firstborn of Hezron <i>were</i> Ram the firstborn, then Bunah, Oren, Ozem <i>and</i> Ahijah.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Jerahmeel had another wife, whose name was Atarah; she was the mother of Onam.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The sons of Ram, the firstborn of Jerahmeel, were Maaz, Jamin and Eker.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The sons of Onam were Shammai and Jada. And the sons of Shammai <i>were</i> Nadab and Abishur.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The name of Abishur’s wife <i>was</i> Abihail, and she bore him Ahban and Molid.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The sons of Nadab <i>were</i> Seled and Appaim, and Seled died without sons.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The son of Appaim <i>was</i> Ishi. And the son of Ishi <i>was</i> Sheshan. And the son of Sheshan <i>was</i> Ahlai.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The sons of Jada the brother of Shammai <i>were</i> Jether and Jonathan, and Jether died without sons.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The sons of Jonathan <i>were</i> Peleth and Zaza. These were the sons of Jerahmeel.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Now Sheshan had no sons, only daughters. And Sheshan had an Egyptian servant whose name was Jarha.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Sheshan gave his daughter to Jarha his servant in marriage, and she bore him Attai.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Attai became the father of Nathan, and Nathan became the father of Zabad,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>and Zabad became the father of Ephlal, and Ephlal became the father of Obed,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>and Obed became the father of Jehu, and Jehu became the father of Azariah,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>and Azariah became the father of Helez, and Helez became the father of Eleasah,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>and Eleasah became the father of Sismai, and Sismai became the father of Shallum,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>and Shallum became the father of Jekamiah, and Jekamiah became the father of Elishama.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Now the sons of Caleb, the brother of Jerahmeel, <i>were</i> Mesha his firstborn, who was the father of Ziph; and his son was Mareshah, the father of Hebron.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>The sons of Hebron <i>were</i> Korah and Tappuah and Rekem and Shema.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Shema became the father of Raham, the father of Jorkeam; and Rekem became the father of Shammai.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>The son of Shammai was Maon, and Maon <i>was</i> the father of Bethzur.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Ephah, Caleb’s concubine, bore Haran, Moza and Gazez; and Haran became the father of Gazez.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>The sons of Jahdai <i>were</i> Regem, Jotham, Geshan, Pelet, Ephah and Shaaph.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Maacah, Caleb’s concubine, bore Sheber and Tirhanah.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>She also bore Shaaph the father of Madmannah, Sheva the father of Machbena and the father of Gibea; and the daughter of Caleb <i>was</i> Achsah.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>These were the sons of Caleb.The sons of Hur, the firstborn of Ephrathah, <i>were</i> Shobal the father of Kiriath-jearim,",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Salma the father of Bethlehem <i>and</i> Hareph the father of Beth-gader.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Shobal the father of Kiriath-jearim had sons: Haroeh, half of the Manahathites,",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>and the families of Kiriath-jearim: the Ithrites, the Puthites, the Shumathites and the Mishraites; from these came the Zorathites and the Eshtaolites.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>The sons of Salma <i>were</i> Bethlehem and the Netophathites, Atroth-beth-joab and half of the Manahathites, the Zorites.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>The families of scribes who lived at Jabez <i>were</i> the Tirathites, the Shimeathites <i>and</i> the Sucathites. Those are the Kenites who came from Hammath, the father of the house of Rechab."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10363A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10363A\"></sup>Now these were the sons of David who were born to him in Hebron: the firstborn <i>was</i> Amnon, by Ahinoam the Jezreelitess; the second <i>was</i> Daniel, by Abigail the Carmelitess;",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>the third <i>was</i> Absalom the son of Maacah, the daughter of Talmai king of Geshur; the fourth <i>was</i> Adonijah the son of Haggith;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>the fifth <i>was</i> Shephatiah, by Abital; the sixth <i>was</i> Ithream, by his wife Eglah.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Six were born to him in Hebron, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10366B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10366B\"></sup>there he reigned seven years and six months. And in Jerusalem he reigned thirty-three years.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10367C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10367C\"></sup>These were born to him in Jerusalem: Shimea, Shobab, Nathan and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10367D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10367D\"></sup>Solomon, four, by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10367E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10367E\"></sup>Bath-shua the daughter of Ammiel;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and Ibhar, Elishama, Eliphelet,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Nogah, Nepheg and Japhia,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Elishama, Eliada and Eliphelet, nine.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>All <i>these were</i> the sons of David, besides the sons of the concubines; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10371F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10371F\"></sup>Tamar <i>was</i> their sister.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now Solomon’s son <i>was</i> Rehoboam, Abijah <i>was</i> his son, Asa his son, Jehoshaphat his son,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Joram his son, Ahaziah his son, Joash his son,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Amaziah his son, Azariah his son, Jotham his son,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Ahaz his son, Hezekiah his son, Manasseh his son,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Amon his son, Josiah his son.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The sons of Josiah <i>were</i> Johanan the firstborn, and the second <i>was</i> Jehoiakim, the third Zedekiah, the fourth Shallum.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The sons of Jehoiakim <i>were</i> Jeconiah his son, Zedekiah his son.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The sons of Jeconiah, the prisoner, <i>were</i> Shealtiel his son,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and Malchiram, Pedaiah, Shenazzar, Jekamiah, Hoshama and Nedabiah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The sons of Pedaiah <i>were</i> Zerubbabel and Shimei. And the sons of Zerubbabel <i>were</i> Meshullam and Hananiah, and Shelomith <i>was</i> their sister;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and Hashubah, Ohel, Berechiah, Hasadiah and Jushab-hesed, five.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The sons of Hananiah <i>were</i> Pelatiah and Jeshaiah, the sons of Rephaiah, the sons of Arnan, the sons of Obadiah, the sons of Shecaniah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The descendants of Shecaniah <i>were</i> Shemaiah, and the sons of Shemaiah: Hattush, Igal, Bariah, Neariah and Shaphat, six.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The sons of Neariah <i>were</i> Elioenai, Hizkiah and Azrikam, three.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The sons of Elioenai <i>were</i> Hodaviah, Eliashib, Pelaiah, Akkub, Johanan, Delaiah and Anani, seven."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10387A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10387A\"></sup>The sons of Judah <i>were</i> Perez, Hezron, Carmi, Hur and Shobal.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Reaiah the son of Shobal became the father of Jahath, and Jahath became the father of Ahumai and Lahad. These <i>were</i> the families of the Zorathites.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>These <i>were</i> the sons of Etam: Jezreel, Ishma and Idbash; and the name of their sister <i>was</i> Hazzelelponi.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Penuel <i>was</i> the father of Gedor, and Ezer the father of Hushah. These <i>were</i> the sons of Hur, the firstborn of Ephrathah, the father of Bethlehem.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Ashhur, the father of Tekoa, had two wives, Helah and Naarah.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Naarah bore him Ahuzzam, Hepher, Temeni and Haahashtari. These were the sons of Naarah.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The sons of Helah <i>were</i> Zereth, Izhar and Ethnan.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Koz became the father of Anub and Zobebah, and the families of Aharhel the son of Harum.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Jabez was more honorable than his brothers, and his mother named him Jabez saying, “Because I bore <i>him</i> with pain.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now Jabez called on the God of Israel, saying, “Oh that You would bless me indeed and enlarge my border, and that Your hand might be with me, and that You would keep <i>me</i> from harm that <i>it</i> may not pain me!” And God granted him what he requested.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Chelub the brother of Shuhah became the father of Mehir, who was the father of Eshton.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Eshton became the father of Beth-rapha and Paseah, and Tehinnah the father of Ir-nahash. These are the men of Recah.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now the sons of Kenaz <i>were</i> Othniel and Seraiah. And the sons of Othniel <i>were</i> Hathath and Meonothai.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Meonothai became the father of Ophrah, and Seraiah became the father of Joab the father of Ge-harashim, for they were craftsmen.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The sons of Caleb the son of Jephunneh <i>were</i> Iru, Elah and Naam; and the son of Elah <i>was</i> Kenaz.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The sons of Jehallelel <i>were</i> Ziph and Ziphah, Tiria and Asarel.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The sons of Ezrah <i>were</i> Jether, Mered, Epher and Jalon. (And these are the sons of Bithia the daughter of Pharaoh, whom Mered took) and she conceived <i>and bore</i> Miriam, Shammai and Ishbah the father of Eshtemoa.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>His Jewish wife bore Jered the father of Gedor, and Heber the father of Soco, and Jekuthiel the father of Zanoah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The sons of the wife of Hodiah, the sister of Naham, <i>were</i> the fathers of Keilah the Garmite and Eshtemoa the Maacathite.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The sons of Shimon <i>were</i> Amnon and Rinnah, Benhanan and Tilon. And the sons of Ishi <i>were</i> Zoheth and Ben-zoheth.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The sons of Shelah the son of Judah <i>were</i> Er the father of Lecah and Laadah the father of Mareshah, and the families of the house of the linen workers at Beth-ashbea;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>and Jokim, the men of Cozeba, Joash, Saraph, who ruled in Moab, and Jashubi-lehem. And the records are ancient.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>These were the potters and the inhabitants of Netaim and Gederah; they lived there with the king for his work.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The sons of Simeon <i>were</i> Nemuel and Jamin, Jarib, Zerah, Shaul;",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Shallum his son, Mibsam his son, Mishma his son.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The sons of Mishma <i>were</i> Hammuel his son, Zaccur his son, Shimei his son.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now Shimei had sixteen sons and six daughters; but his brothers did not have many sons, nor did all their family multiply like the sons of Judah.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They lived at Beersheba, Moladah and Hazar-shual,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>at Bilhah, Ezem, Tolad,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Bethuel, Hormah, Ziklag,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Beth-marcaboth, Hazar-susim, Beth-biri and Shaaraim. These <i>were</i> their cities until the reign of David.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Their villages <i>were</i> Etam, Ain, Rimmon, Tochen and Ashan, five cities;",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>and all their villages that <i>were</i> around the same cities as far as Baal. These <i>were</i> their settlements, and they have their genealogy.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Meshobab and Jamlech and Joshah the son of Amaziah,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>and Joel and Jehu the son of Joshibiah, the son of Seraiah, the son of Asiel,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>and Elioenai, Jaakobah, Jeshohaiah, Asaiah, Adiel, Jesimiel, Benaiah,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Ziza the son of Shiphi, the son of Allon, the son of Jedaiah, the son of Shimri, the son of Shemaiah;",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>these mentioned by name <i>were</i> leaders in their families; and their fathers’ houses increased greatly.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>They went to the entrance of Gedor, even to the east side of the valley, to seek pasture for their flocks.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>They found rich and good pasture, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10426B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10426B\"></sup>the land was broad and quiet and peaceful; for those who lived there formerly <i>were</i> Hamites.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10427C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10427C\"></sup>These, recorded by name, came in the days of Hezekiah king of Judah, and attacked their tents and the Meunites who were found there, and destroyed them utterly to this day, and lived in their place, because there was pasture there for their flocks.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>From them, from the sons of Simeon, five hundred men went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10428D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10428D\"></sup>Mount Seir, with Pelatiah, Neariah, Rephaiah and Uzziel, the sons of Ishi, as their leaders.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10429E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10429E\"></sup>They destroyed the remnant of the Amalekites who escaped, and have lived there to this day."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>Now the sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel (for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10430A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10430A\"></sup>he was the firstborn, but because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10430B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10430B\"></sup>he defiled his father’s bed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10430C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10430C\"></sup>his birthright was given to the sons of Joseph the son of Israel; so that he is not enrolled in the genealogy according to the birthright.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10431D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10431D\"></sup>Though Judah prevailed over his brothers, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10431E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10431E\"></sup>from him <i>came</i> the leader, yet the birthright belonged to Joseph),",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10432F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10432F\"></sup>the sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel <i>were</i> Hanoch and Pallu, Hezron and Carmi.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The sons of Joel <i>were</i> Shemaiah his son, Gog his son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10433G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10433G\"></sup>Shimei his son,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Micah his son, Reaiah his son, Baal his son,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Beerah his son, whom Tilgath-pilneser king of Assyria carried away into exile; he was leader of the Reubenites.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>His kinsmen by their families, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10436H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10436H\"></sup>in the genealogy of their generations, <i>were</i> Jeiel the chief, then Zechariah",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and Bela the son of Azaz, the son of Shema, the son of Joel, who lived in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10437I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10437I\"></sup>Aroer, even to Nebo and Baal-meon.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>To the east he settled as far as the entrance of the wilderness from the river Euphrates, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10438J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10438J\"></sup>because their cattle had increased in the land of Gilead.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>In the days of Saul <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10439K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10439K\"></sup>they made war with the Hagrites, who fell by their hand, so that they occupied their tents throughout all the land east of Gilead.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now the sons of Gad lived opposite them in the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10440L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10440L\"></sup>Bashan as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10440M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10440M\"></sup>Salecah.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Joel <i>was</i> the chief and Shapham the second, then Janai and Shaphat in Bashan.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Their kinsmen of their fathers’ households <i>were</i> Michael, Meshullam, Sheba, Jorai, Jacan, Zia and Eber, seven.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>These <i>were</i> the sons of Abihail, the son of Huri, the son of Jaroah, the son of Gilead, the son of Michael, the son of Jeshishai, the son of Jahdo, the son of Buz;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Ahi the son of Abdiel, the son of Guni, <i>was</i> head of their fathers’ households.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>They lived in Gilead, in Bashan and in its towns, and in all the pasture lands of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10445N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10445N\"></sup>Sharon, as far as their borders.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>All of these were enrolled in the genealogies in the days of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10446O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10446O\"></sup>Jotham king of Judah and in the days of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10446P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10446P\"></sup>Jeroboam king of Israel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The sons of Reuben and the Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh, <i>consisting</i> of valiant men, men who bore shield and sword and shot with bow and <i>were</i> skillful in battle, <i>were</i> 44,760, who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10447Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10447Q\"></sup>went to war.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They made war against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10448R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10448R\"></sup>the Hagrites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10448S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10448S\"></sup>Jetur, Naphish and Nodab.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>They were helped against them, and the Hagrites and all who <i>were</i> with them were given into their hand; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10449T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10449T\"></sup>they cried out to God in the battle, and He answered their prayers because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10449U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10449U\"></sup>they trusted in Him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They took away their cattle: their 50,000 camels, 250,000 sheep, 2,000 donkeys; and 100,000 men.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For many fell slain, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10451V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10451V\"></sup>the war <i>was</i> of God. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10451W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10451W\"></sup>they settled in their place until the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10451X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10451X\"></sup>exile.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now the sons of the half-tribe of Manasseh lived in the land; from Bashan to Baal-hermon and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10452Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10452Y\"></sup>Senir and Mount Hermon they were numerous.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>These were the heads of their fathers’ households, even Epher, Ishi, Eliel, Azriel, Jeremiah, Hodaviah and Jahdiel, mighty men of valor, famous men, heads of their fathers’ households.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10454Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10454Z\"></sup>acted treacherously against the God of their fathers and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10454AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10454AA\"></sup>played the harlot <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10454AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10454AB\"></sup>after the gods of the peoples of the land, whom God had destroyed before them.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So the God of Israel stirred up the spirit of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10455AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10455AC\"></sup>Pul, king of Assyria, even the spirit of Tilgath-pilneser king of Assyria, and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10455AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10455AD\"></sup>carried them away into exile, namely the Reubenites, the Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh, and brought them to Halah, Habor, Hara and to the river of Gozan, to this day."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10456A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10456A\"></sup>The sons of Levi <i>were</i> Gershon, Kohath and Merari.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The sons of Kohath <i>were</i> Amram, Izhar, Hebron and Uzziel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The children of Amram <i>were</i> Aaron, Moses and Miriam. And the sons of Aaron <i>were</i> Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar and Ithamar.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Eleazar became the father of Phinehas, <i>and</i> Phinehas became the father of Abishua,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and Abishua became the father of Bukki, and Bukki became the father of Uzzi,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and Uzzi became the father of Zerahiah, and Zerahiah became the father of Meraioth,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Meraioth became the father of Amariah, and Amariah became the father of Ahitub,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10463B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10463B\"></sup>Ahitub became the father of Zadok, and Zadok <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10463C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10463C\"></sup>became the father of Ahimaaz,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and Ahimaaz became the father of Azariah, and Azariah became the father of Johanan,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and Johanan became the father of Azariah (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10465D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10465D\"></sup>it was he who served as the priest in the house <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10465E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10465E\"></sup>which Solomon built in Jerusalem),",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10466F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10466F\"></sup>Azariah became the father of Amariah, and Amariah became the father of Ahitub,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and Ahitub became the father of Zadok, and Zadok became the father of Shallum,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and Shallum became the father of Hilkiah, and Hilkiah became the father of Azariah,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and Azariah became the father of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10469G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10469G\"></sup>Seraiah, and Seraiah became the father of Jehozadak;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and Jehozadak went <i>along</i> when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> carried Judah and Jerusalem away into exile by Nebuchadnezzar.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10471H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10471H\"></sup>The sons of Levi <i>were</i> Gershom, Kohath and Merari.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>These are the names of the sons of Gershom: Libni and Shimei.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The sons of Kohath <i>were</i> Amram, Izhar, Hebron and Uzziel.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10474I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10474I\"></sup>Merari <i>were</i> Mahli and Mushi. And these are the families of the Levites according to their fathers’ <i>households</i>.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Of Gershom: Libni his son, Jahath his son, Zimmah his son,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Joah his son, Iddo his son, Zerah his son, Jeatherai his son.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The sons of Kohath <i>were</i> Amminadab his son, Korah his son, Assir his son,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Elkanah his son, Ebiasaph his son and Assir his son,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Tahath his son, Uriel his son, Uzziah his son and Shaul his son.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The sons of Elkanah <i>were</i> Amasai and Ahimoth.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><i>As for</i> Elkanah, the sons of Elkanah <i>were</i> Zophai his son and Nahath his son,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Eliab his son, Jeroham his son, Elkanah his son.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The sons of Samuel <i>were</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10483J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10483J\"></sup>Joel the firstborn, and Abijah the second.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The sons of Merari <i>were</i> Mahli, Libni his son, Shimei his son, Uzzah his son,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Shimea his son, Haggiah his son, Asaiah his son.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10486K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10486K\"></sup>Now these are those whom David appointed over the service of song in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10486L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10486L\"></sup>after the ark rested <i>there</i>.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>They ministered with song before the tabernacle of the tent of meeting, until Solomon had built the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Jerusalem; and they served in their office according to their order.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>These are those who served with their sons: From the sons of the Kohathites <i>were</i> Heman the singer, the son of Joel, the son of Samuel,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>the son of Elkanah, the son of Jeroham, the son of Eliel, the son of Toah,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>the son of Zuph, the son of Elkanah, the son of Mahath, the son of Amasai,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>the son of Elkanah, the son of Joel, the son of Azariah, the son of Zephaniah,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>the son of Tahath, the son of Assir, the son of Ebiasaph, the son of Korah,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>the son of Izhar, the son of Kohath, the son of Levi, the son of Israel.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><i>Heman’s</i> brother Asaph stood at his right hand, even Asaph the son of Berechiah, the son of Shimea,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>the son of Michael, the son of Baaseiah, the son of Malchijah,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>the son of Ethni, the son of Zerah, the son of Adaiah,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>the son of Ethan, the son of Zimmah, the son of Shimei,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>the son of Jahath, the son of Gershom, the son of Levi.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>On the left hand <i>were</i> their kinsmen the sons of Merari: Ethan the son of Kishi, the son of Abdi, the son of Malluch,",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>the son of Hashabiah, the son of Amaziah, the son of Hilkiah,",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>the son of Amzi, the son of Bani, the son of Shemer,",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>the son of Mahli, the son of Mushi, the son of Merari, the son of Levi.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Their kinsmen the Levites were appointed for all the service of the tabernacle of the house of God.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>But Aaron and his sons <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10504M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10504M\"></sup>offered on the altar of burnt offering and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10504N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10504N\"></sup>on the altar of incense, for all the work of the most holy place, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10504O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10504O\"></sup>to make atonement for Israel, according to all that Moses the servant of God had commanded.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10505P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10505P\"></sup>These are the sons of Aaron: Eleazar his son, Phinehas his son, Abishua his son,",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Bukki his son, Uzzi his son, Zerahiah his son,",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Meraioth his son, Amariah his son, Ahitub his son,",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>Zadok his son, Ahimaaz his son.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>Now these are their settlements according to their camps within their borders. To the sons of Aaron of the families of the Kohathites (for theirs was the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10509Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10509Q\"></sup><i>first</i> lot),",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>to them they gave <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10510R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10510R\"></sup>Hebron in the land of Judah and its pasture lands around it;",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10511S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10511S\"></sup>but the fields of the city and its villages, they gave to Caleb the son of Jephunneh.",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10512T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10512T\"></sup>To the sons of Aaron they gave the <i>following</i> cities of refuge: Hebron, Libnah also with its pasture lands, Jattir, Eshtemoa with its pasture lands,",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>Hilen with its pasture lands, Debir with its pasture lands,",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>Ashan with its pasture lands and Beth-shemesh with its pasture lands;",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>and from the tribe of Benjamin: Geba with its pasture lands, Allemeth with its pasture lands, and Anathoth with its pasture lands. All their cities throughout their families were thirteen cities.",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10516U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10516U\"></sup>Then to the rest of the sons of Kohath <i>were given</i> by lot, from the family of the tribe, from the half-tribe, the half of Manasseh, ten cities.",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>To the sons of Gershom, according to their families, <i>were given</i> from the tribe of Issachar and from the tribe of Asher, the tribe of Naphtali, and the tribe of Manasseh, thirteen cities in Bashan.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10518V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10518V\"></sup>To the sons of Merari <i>were given</i> by lot, according to their families, from the tribe of Reuben, the tribe of Gad and the tribe of Zebulun, twelve cities.",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10519W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10519W\"></sup>So the sons of Israel gave to the Levites the cities with their pasture lands.",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>They gave by lot from the tribe of the sons of Judah, the tribe of the sons of Simeon and the tribe of the sons of Benjamin, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10520X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10520X\"></sup>these cities which are mentioned by name.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10521Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10521Y\"></sup>Now some of the families of the sons of Kohath had cities of their territory from the tribe of Ephraim.",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup>They gave to them the <i>following</i> cities of refuge: Shechem in the hill country of Ephraim with its pasture lands, Gezer also with its pasture lands,",
			"68": "<sup class=\"versenum\">68 </sup>Jokmeam with its pasture lands, Beth-horon with its pasture lands,",
			"69": "<sup class=\"versenum\">69 </sup>Aijalon with its pasture lands and Gath-rimmon with its pasture lands;",
			"70": "<sup class=\"versenum\">70 </sup>and from the half-tribe of Manasseh: Aner with its pasture lands and Bileam with its pasture lands, for the rest of the family of the sons of Kohath.",
			"71": "<sup class=\"versenum\">71 </sup>To the sons of Gershom <i>were given</i>, from the family of the half-tribe of Manasseh: Golan in Bashan with its pasture lands and Ashtaroth with its pasture lands;",
			"72": "<sup class=\"versenum\">72 </sup>and from the tribe of Issachar: Kedesh with its pasture lands, Daberath with its pasture lands",
			"73": "<sup class=\"versenum\">73 </sup>and Ramoth with its pasture lands, Anem with its pasture lands;",
			"74": "<sup class=\"versenum\">74 </sup>and from the tribe of Asher: Mashal with its pasture lands, Abdon with its pasture lands,",
			"75": "<sup class=\"versenum\">75 </sup>Hukok with its pasture lands and Rehob with its pasture lands;",
			"76": "<sup class=\"versenum\">76 </sup>and from the tribe of Naphtali: Kedesh in Galilee with its pasture lands, Hammon with its pasture lands and Kiriathaim with its pasture lands.",
			"77": "<sup class=\"versenum\">77 </sup>To the rest of <i>the Levites</i>, the sons of Merari, <i>were given</i>, from the tribe of Zebulun: Rimmono with its pasture lands, Tabor with its pasture lands;",
			"78": "<sup class=\"versenum\">78 </sup>and beyond the Jordan at Jericho, on the east side of the Jordan, <i>were given them</i>, from the tribe of Reuben: Bezer in the wilderness with its pasture lands, Jahzah with its pasture lands,",
			"79": "<sup class=\"versenum\">79 </sup>Kedemoth with its pasture lands and Mephaath with its pasture lands;",
			"80": "<sup class=\"versenum\">80 </sup>and from the tribe of Gad: Ramoth in Gilead with its pasture lands, Mahanaim with its pasture lands,",
			"81": "<sup class=\"versenum\">81 </sup>Heshbon with its pasture lands and Jazer with its pasture lands."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>Now the sons of Issachar <i>were</i> four: Tola, Puah, Jashub and Shimron.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The sons of Tola <i>were</i> Uzzi, Rephaiah, Jeriel, Jahmai, Ibsam and Samuel, heads of their fathers’ households. <i>The sons</i> of Tola <i>were</i> mighty men of valor in their generations; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10538A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10538A\"></sup>their number in the days of David was 22,600.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The son of Uzzi <i>was</i> Izrahiah. And the sons of Izrahiah <i>were</i> Michael, Obadiah, Joel, Isshiah; all five of them <i>were</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10539B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10539B\"></sup>chief men.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>With them by their generations according to their fathers’ households were 36,000 troops of the army for war, for they had many wives and sons.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Their relatives among all the families of Issachar <i>were</i> mighty men of valor, enrolled by genealogy, in all 87,000.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10542C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10542C\"></sup><i>The sons of</i> Benjamin <i>were</i> three: Bela and Becher and Jediael.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The sons of Bela were five: Ezbon, Uzzi, Uzziel, Jerimoth and Iri. They <i>were</i> heads of fathers’ households, mighty men of valor, and were 22,034 enrolled by genealogy.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The sons of Becher <i>were</i> Zemirah, Joash, Eliezer, Elioenai, Omri, Jeremoth, Abijah, Anathoth and Alemeth. All these <i>were</i> the sons of Becher.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They were enrolled by genealogy, according to their generations, heads of their fathers’ households, 20,200 mighty men of valor.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The son of Jediael <i>was</i> Bilhan. And the sons of Bilhan <i>were</i> Jeush, Benjamin, Ehud, Chenaanah, Zethan, Tarshish and Ahishahar.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>All these <i>were</i> sons of Jediael, according to the heads of their fathers’ households, 17,200 mighty men of valor, who were ready to go out with the army to war.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Shuppim and Huppim <i>were</i> the sons of Ir; Hushim <i>was</i> the son of Aher.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The sons of Naphtali <i>were</i> Jahziel, Guni, Jezer, and Shallum, the sons of Bilhah.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The sons of Manasseh <i>were</i> Asriel, whom his Aramean concubine bore; she bore Machir the father of Gilead.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Machir took a wife for Huppim and Shuppim, whose sister’s name was Maacah. And the name of the second was Zelophehad, and Zelophehad had daughters.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Maacah the wife of Machir bore a son, and she named him Peresh; and the name of his brother <i>was</i> Sheresh, and his sons <i>were</i> Ulam and Rakem.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The son of Ulam <i>was</i> Bedan. These <i>were</i> the sons of Gilead the son of Machir, the son of Manasseh.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>His sister Hammolecheth bore Ishhod and Abiezer and Mahlah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The sons of Shemida were Ahian and Shechem and Likhi and Aniam.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10556D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10556D\"></sup>The sons of Ephraim <i>were</i> Shuthelah and Bered his son, Tahath his son, Eleadah his son, Tahath his son,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Zabad his son, Shuthelah his son, and Ezer and Elead whom the men of Gath who were born in the land killed, because they came down to take their livestock.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Their father Ephraim <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10558E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10558E\"></sup>mourned many days, and his relatives <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10558F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10558F\"></sup>came to comfort him.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then he went in to his wife, and she conceived and bore a son, and he named him Beriah, because misfortune had come upon his house.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>His daughter was Sheerah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10560G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10560G\"></sup>who built lower and upper Beth-horon, also Uzzen-sheerah.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Rephah was his son <i>along</i> with Resheph, Telah his son, Tahan his son,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Ladan his son, Ammihud his son, Elishama his son,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Non his son and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10563H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10563H\"></sup>Joshua his son.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10564I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10564I\"></sup>Their possessions and settlements <i>were</i> Bethel with its towns, and to the east Naaran, and to the west Gezer with its towns, and Shechem with its towns as far as Ayyah with its towns,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>and along the borders of the sons of Manasseh, Beth-shean with its towns, Taanach with its towns, Megiddo with its towns, Dor with its towns. In these lived the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10565J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10565J\"></sup>sons of Joseph the son of Israel.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10566K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10566K\"></sup>The sons of Asher <i>were</i> Imnah, Ishvah, Ishvi and Beriah, and Serah their sister.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The sons of Beriah <i>were</i> Heber and Malchiel, who was the father of Birzaith.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Heber became the father of Japhlet, Shomer and Hotham, and Shua their sister.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The sons of Japhlet <i>were</i> Pasach, Bimhal and Ashvath. These were the sons of Japhlet.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The sons of Shemer <i>were</i> Ahi and Rohgah, Jehubbah and Aram.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The sons of his brother Helem <i>were</i> Zophah, Imna, Shelesh and Amal.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>The sons of Zophah <i>were</i> Suah, Harnepher, Shual, Beri and Imrah,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Bezer, Hod, Shamma, Shilshah, Ithran and Beera.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>The sons of Jether <i>were</i> Jephunneh, Pispa and Ara.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>The sons of Ulla <i>were</i> Arah, Hanniel and Rizia.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>All these <i>were</i> the sons of Asher, heads of the fathers’ houses, choice and mighty men of valor, heads of the princes. And the number of them enrolled by genealogy for service in war was 26,000 men."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10577A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10577A\"></sup>Benjamin became the father of Bela his firstborn, Ashbel the second, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10577B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10577B\"></sup>Aharah the third,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Nohah the fourth and Rapha the fifth.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Bela had sons: Addar, Gera, Abihud,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Abishua, Naaman, Ahoah,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Gera, Shephuphan and Huram.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>These are the sons of Ehud: these are the heads of fathers’ <i>households</i> of the inhabitants of Geba, and they carried them into exile to Manahath,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>namely, Naaman, Ahijah and Gera—he carried them into exile; and he became the father of Uzza and Ahihud.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Shaharaim became the father of children in the country of Moab after he had sent away Hushim and Baara his wives.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>By Hodesh his wife he became the father of Jobab, Zibia, Mesha, Malcam,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Jeuz, Sachia, Mirmah. These were his sons, heads of fathers’ <i>households</i>.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>By Hushim he became the father of Abitub and Elpaal.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The sons of Elpaal <i>were</i> Eber, Misham, and Shemed, who built Ono and Lod, with its towns;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and Beriah and Shema, who were heads of fathers’ <i>households</i> of the inhabitants of Aijalon, who put to flight the inhabitants of Gath;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and Ahio, Shashak and Jeremoth.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Zebadiah, Arad, Eder,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Michael, Ishpah and Joha <i>were</i> the sons of Beriah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Zebadiah, Meshullam, Hizki, Heber,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Ishmerai, Izliah and Jobab <i>were</i> the sons of Elpaal.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Jakim, Zichri, Zabdi,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Elienai, Zillethai, Eliel,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Adaiah, Beraiah and Shimrath <i>were</i> the sons of Shimei.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Ishpan, Eber, Eliel,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Abdon, Zichri, Hanan,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Hananiah, Elam, Anthothijah,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Iphdeiah and Penuel <i>were</i> the sons of Shashak.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Shamsherai, Shehariah, Athaliah,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Jaareshiah, Elijah and Zichri <i>were</i> the sons of Jeroham.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>These were heads of the fathers’ <i>households</i> according to their generations, chief men who lived in Jerusalem.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10605C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10605C\"></sup>Now in Gibeon, <i>Jeiel</i>, the father of Gibeon lived, and his wife’s name was Maacah;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>and his firstborn son <i>was</i> Abdon, then Zur, Kish, Baal, Nadab,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Gedor, Ahio and Zecher.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Mikloth became the father of Shimeah. And they also lived with their relatives in Jerusalem opposite their <i>other</i> relatives.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10609D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10609D\"></sup>Ner became the father of Kish, and Kish became the father of Saul, and Saul became the father of Jonathan, Malchi-shua, Abinadab and Eshbaal.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The son of Jonathan <i>was</i> Merib-baal, and Merib-baal became the father of Micah.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The sons of Micah <i>were</i> Pithon, Melech, Tarea and Ahaz.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Ahaz became the father of Jehoaddah, and Jehoaddah became the father of Alemeth, Azmaveth and Zimri; and Zimri became the father of Moza.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Moza became the father of Binea; Raphah <i>was</i> his son, Eleasah his son, Azel his son.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Azel had six sons, and these <i>were</i> their names: Azrikam, Bocheru, Ishmael, Sheariah, Obadiah and Hanan. All these <i>were</i> the sons of Azel.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>The sons of Eshek his brother <i>were</i> Ulam his firstborn, Jeush the second and Eliphelet the third.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The sons of Ulam were mighty men of valor, archers, and had many sons and grandsons, 150 <i>of them</i>. All these <i>were</i> of the sons of Benjamin."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>So all Israel was enrolled by genealogies; and behold, they are written in the Book of the Kings of Israel. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10617A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10617A\"></sup>Judah was carried away into exile to Babylon for their unfaithfulness.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10618B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10618B\"></sup>Now the first who lived in their possessions in their cities <i>were</i> Israel, the priests, the Levites and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10618C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10618C\"></sup>the temple servants.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Some of the sons of Judah, of the sons of Benjamin and of the sons of Ephraim and Manasseh lived in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10619D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10619D\"></sup>Jerusalem:",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Uthai the son of Ammihud, the son of Omri, the son of Imri, the son of Bani, from the sons of Perez the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10620E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10620E\"></sup>son of Judah.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>From the Shilonites <i>were</i> Asaiah the firstborn and his sons.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>From the sons of Zerah <i>were</i> Jeuel and their relatives, 690 <i>of them</i>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>From the sons of Benjamin <i>were</i> Sallu the son of Meshullam, the son of Hodaviah, the son of Hassenuah,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and Ibneiah the son of Jeroham, and Elah the son of Uzzi, the son of Michri, and Meshullam the son of Shephatiah, the son of Reuel, the son of Ibnijah;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and their relatives according to their generations, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10625F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10625F\"></sup>956. All these <i>were</i> heads of fathers’ <i>households</i> according to their fathers’ houses.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10626G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10626G\"></sup>From the priests <i>were</i> Jedaiah, Jehoiarib, Jachin,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and Azariah the son of Hilkiah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Zadok, the son of Meraioth, the son of Ahitub, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10627H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10627H\"></sup>the chief officer of the house of God;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and Adaiah the son of Jeroham, the son of Pashhur, the son of Malchijah, and Maasai the son of Adiel, the son of Jahzerah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Meshillemith, the son of Immer;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and their relatives, heads of their fathers’ households, 1,760 very able men for the work of the service of the house of God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10630I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10630I\"></sup>Of the Levites <i>were</i> Shemaiah the son of Hasshub, the son of Azrikam, the son of Hashabiah, of the sons of Merari;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and Bakbakkar, Heresh and Galal and Mattaniah the son of Mica, the son of Zichri, the son of Asaph,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and Obadiah the son of Shemaiah, the son of Galal, the son of Jeduthun, and Berechiah the son of Asa, the son of Elkanah, who lived in the villages of the Netophathites.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now the gatekeepers <i>were</i> Shallum and Akkub and Talmon and Ahiman and their relatives (Shallum the chief",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><i>being stationed</i> until now at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10634J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10634J\"></sup>the king’s gate to the east). These <i>were</i> the gatekeepers for the camp of the sons of Levi.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Shallum the son of Kore, the son of Ebiasaph, the son of Korah, and his relatives of his father’s house, the Korahites, <i>were</i> over the work of the service, keepers of the thresholds of the tent; and their fathers had been over the camp of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, keepers of the entrance.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10636K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10636K\"></sup>Phinehas the son of Eleazar was ruler over them previously, <i>and</i> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10637L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10637L\"></sup>Zechariah the son of Meshelemiah was gatekeeper of the entrance of the tent of meeting.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>All these who were chosen to be gatekeepers at the thresholds were 212. These were enrolled by genealogy in their villages, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10638M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10638M\"></sup>whom David and Samuel the seer appointed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10638N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10638N\"></sup>in their office of trust.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So they and their sons had charge of the gates of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <i>even</i> the house of the tent, as guards.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The gatekeepers were on the four sides, to the east, west, north and south.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Their relatives in their villages <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10641O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10641O\"></sup><i>were</i> to come in every seven days from time to time <i>to be</i> with them;",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>for the four chief gatekeepers who <i>were</i> Levites, were in an office of trust, and were over the chambers and over the treasuries in the house of God.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>They spent the night around the house of God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10643P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10643P\"></sup>because the watch was committed to them; and they <i>were</i> in charge of opening <i>it</i> morning by morning.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now some of them had charge of the utensils of service, for they counted them when they brought them in and when they took them out.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Some of them also were appointed over the furniture and over all the utensils of the sanctuary and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10645Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10645Q\"></sup>over the fine flour and the wine and the oil and the frankincense and the spices.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Some of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10646R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10646R\"></sup>the sons of the priests prepared the mixing of the spices.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Mattithiah, one of the Levites, who was the firstborn of Shallum the Korahite, had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10647S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10647S\"></sup>the responsibility over the things which were baked in pans.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Some of their relatives of the sons of the Kohathites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10648T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10648T\"></sup><i>were</i> over the showbread to prepare it every sabbath.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Now these are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10649U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10649U\"></sup>the singers, heads of fathers’ <i>households</i> of the Levites, <i>who lived</i> in the chambers <i>of the temple</i> free <i>from other service</i>; for they were engaged <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10649V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10649V\"></sup>in their work day and night.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>These were heads of fathers’ <i>households</i> of the Levites according to their generations, chief men, who lived in Jerusalem.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10651W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10651W\"></sup>In Gibeon Jeiel the father of Gibeon lived, and his wife’s name was Maacah,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>and his firstborn son <i>was</i> Abdon, then Zur, Kish, Baal, Ner, Nadab,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Gedor, Ahio, Zechariah and Mikloth.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Mikloth became the father of Shimeam. And they also lived with their relatives in Jerusalem opposite their <i>other</i> relatives.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10655X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10655X\"></sup>Ner became the father of Kish, and Kish became the father of Saul, and Saul became the father of Jonathan, Malchi-shua, Abinadab and Eshbaal.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The son of Jonathan <i>was</i> Merib-baal; and Merib-baal became the father of Micah.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>The sons of Micah <i>were</i> Pithon, Melech, Tahrea <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10657Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10657Y\"></sup><i>and Ahaz</i>.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Ahaz became the father of Jarah, and Jarah became the father of Alemeth, Azmaveth and Zimri; and Zimri became the father of Moza,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>and Moza became the father of Binea and Rephaiah his son, Eleasah his son, Azel his son.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Azel had six sons whose names are these: Azrikam, Bocheru and Ishmael and Sheariah and Obadiah and Hanan. These were the sons of Azel."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10661A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10661A\"></sup>Now the Philistines fought against Israel; and the men of Israel fled before the Philistines and fell slain on Mount Gilboa.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The Philistines closely pursued Saul and his sons, and the Philistines struck down Jonathan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10662B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10662B\"></sup>Abinadab and Malchi-shua, the sons of Saul.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The battle became heavy against Saul, and the archers overtook him; and he was wounded by the archers.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Saul said to his armor bearer, “Draw your sword and thrust me through with it, otherwise these uncircumcised will come and abuse me.” But his armor bearer would not, for he was greatly afraid. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10664C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10664C\"></sup>Therefore Saul took his sword and fell on it.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When his armor bearer saw that Saul was dead, he likewise fell on his sword and died.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10666D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10666D\"></sup>Thus Saul died with his three sons, and all <i>those</i> of his house died together.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When all the men of Israel who were in the valley saw that they had fled, and that Saul and his sons were dead, they forsook their cities and fled; and the Philistines came and lived in them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>It came about the next day, when the Philistines came to strip the slain, that they found Saul and his sons fallen on Mount Gilboa.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10669E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10669E\"></sup>So they stripped him and took his head and his armor and sent <i>messengers</i> around the land of the Philistines to carry the good news to their idols and to the people.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They put his armor in the house of their gods and fastened his head in the house of Dagon.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When all Jabesh-gilead heard all that the Philistines had done to Saul,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10672F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10672F\"></sup>all the valiant men arose and took away the body of Saul and the bodies of his sons and brought them to Jabesh, and they buried their bones under the oak in Jabesh, and fasted seven days.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10673G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10673G\"></sup>So Saul died for his trespass which he committed against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, because of the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which he did not keep; and also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10673H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10673H\"></sup>because he asked counsel of a medium, making inquiry <i>of it</i>,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and did not inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Therefore He killed him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10674I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10674I\"></sup>turned the kingdom to David the son of Jesse."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10675A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10675A\"></sup>Then all Israel gathered to David at Hebron and said, “Behold, we are your bone and your flesh.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>In times past, even when Saul was king, you <i>were</i> the one who led out and brought in Israel; and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God said to you, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10676B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10676B\"></sup>You shall shepherd My people Israel, and you shall be prince over My people Israel.’”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So all the elders of Israel came to the king at Hebron, and David made a covenant with them in Hebron before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10677C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10677C\"></sup>they anointed David king over Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10677D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10677D\"></sup>according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> through Samuel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then David and all Israel went to Jerusalem (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10678E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10678E\"></sup>that is, Jebus); and the Jebusites, the inhabitants of the land, <i>were</i> there.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The inhabitants of Jebus said to David, “You shall not enter here.” Nevertheless David captured the stronghold of Zion (that is, the city of David).",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now David had said, “Whoever strikes down a Jebusite first shall be chief and commander.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10680F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10680F\"></sup>Joab the son of Zeruiah went up first, so he became chief.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then David dwelt in the stronghold; therefore it was called the city of David.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He built the city all around, from the Millo even to the surrounding area; and Joab repaired the rest of the city.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10683G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10683G\"></sup>David became greater and greater, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts <i>was</i> with him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10684H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10684H\"></sup>Now these are the heads of the mighty men whom David had, who gave him strong support in his kingdom, together with all Israel, to make him king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10684I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10684I\"></sup>according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> concerning Israel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>These <i>constitute</i> the list of the mighty men whom David had: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10685J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10685J\"></sup>Jashobeam, the son of a Hachmonite, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10685K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10685K\"></sup>the chief of the thirty; he lifted up his spear against three hundred whom he killed at one time.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>After him was Eleazar the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10686L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10686L\"></sup>Dodo, the Ahohite, who <i>was</i> one of the three mighty men.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He was with David at Pasdammim <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10687M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10687M\"></sup>when the Philistines were gathered together there to battle, and there was a plot of ground full of barley; and the people fled before the Philistines.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They took their stand in the midst of the plot and defended it, and struck down the Philistines; and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saved them by a great victory.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now three of the thirty chief men went down to the rock to David, into the cave of Adullam, while <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10689N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10689N\"></sup>the army of the Philistines was camping in the valley of Rephaim.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>David was then in the stronghold, while <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10690O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10690O\"></sup>the garrison of the Philistines <i>was</i> then in Bethlehem.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>David had a craving and said, “Oh that someone would give me water to drink from the well of Bethlehem, which is by the gate!”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So the three broke through the camp of the Philistines and drew water from the well of Bethlehem which <i>was</i> by the gate, and took <i>it</i> and brought <i>it</i> to David; nevertheless David would not drink it, but poured it out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and he said, “Be it far from me before my God that I should do this. Shall I drink the blood of these men <i>who went</i> at the risk of their lives? For at the risk of their lives they brought it.” Therefore he would not drink it. These things the three mighty men did.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>As for Abshai the brother of Joab, he was chief of the thirty, and he swung his spear against three hundred and killed them; and he had a name as well as the thirty.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Of the three in the second <i>rank</i> he was the most honored and became their commander; however, he did not attain to the <i>first</i> three.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10696P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10696P\"></sup>Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, the son of a valiant man of Kabzeel, mighty in deeds, struck down the two <i>sons of</i> Ariel of Moab. He also went down and killed a lion inside a pit on a snowy day.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He killed an Egyptian, a man of <i>great</i> stature five cubits tall. Now in the Egyptian’s hand <i>was</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10697Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10697Q\"></sup>a spear like a weaver’s beam, but he went down to him with a club and snatched the spear from the Egyptian’s hand and killed him with his own spear.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>These <i>things</i> Benaiah the son of Jehoiada did, and had a name as well as the three mighty men.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Behold, he was honored among the thirty, but he did not attain to the three; and David appointed him over his guard.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now the mighty men of the armies <i>were</i> Asahel the brother of Joab, Elhanan the son of Dodo of Bethlehem,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Shammoth the Harorite, Helez the Pelonite,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Ira the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite, Abiezer the Anathothite,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Sibbecai the Hushathite, Ilai the Ahohite,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Maharai the Netophathite, Heled the son of Baanah the Netophathite,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Ithai the son of Ribai of Gibeah of the sons of Benjamin, Benaiah the Pirathonite,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Hurai of the brooks of Gaash, Abiel the Arbathite,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Azmaveth the Baharumite, Eliahba the Shaalbonite,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>the sons of Hashem the Gizonite, Jonathan the son of Shagee the Hararite,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Ahiam the son of Sacar the Hararite, Eliphal the son of Ur,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Hepher the Mecherathite, Ahijah the Pelonite,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Hezro the Carmelite, Naarai the son of Ezbai,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Joel the brother of Nathan, Mibhar the son of Hagri,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Zelek the Ammonite, Naharai the Berothite, the armor bearer of Joab the son of Zeruiah,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Ira the Ithrite, Gareb the Ithrite,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Uriah the Hittite, Zabad the son of Ahlai,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Adina the son of Shiza the Reubenite, a chief of the Reubenites, and thirty with him,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Hanan the son of Maacah and Joshaphat the Mithnite,",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Uzzia the Ashterathite, Shama and Jeiel the sons of Hotham the Aroerite,",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Jediael the son of Shimri and Joha his brother, the Tizite,",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Eliel the Mahavite and Jeribai and Joshaviah, the sons of Elnaam, and Ithmah the Moabite,",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Eliel and Obed and Jaasiel the Mezobaite."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10722A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10722A\"></sup>Now these are the ones who came to David at Ziklag, while he was still restricted because of Saul the son of Kish; and they were among the mighty men who helped <i>him</i> in war.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>They were equipped with bows, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10723B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10723B\"></sup>using both the right hand and the left <i>to sling</i> stones and <i>to shoot</i> arrows from the bow; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10723C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10723C\"></sup><i>they were</i> Saul’s kinsmen from Benjamin.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The chief was Ahiezer, then Joash, the sons of Shemaah the Gibeathite; and Jeziel and Pelet, the sons of Azmaveth, and Beracah and Jehu the Anathothite,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and Ishmaiah the Gibeonite, a mighty man among the thirty, and over the thirty. Then Jeremiah, Jahaziel, Johanan, Jozabad the Gederathite,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Eluzai, Jerimoth, Bealiah, Shemariah, Shephatiah the Haruphite,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Elkanah, Isshiah, Azarel, Joezer, Jashobeam, the Korahites,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and Joelah and Zebadiah, the sons of Jeroham of Gedor.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>From the Gadites there came over to David in the stronghold in the wilderness, mighty men of valor, men trained for war, who could handle shield and spear, and whose faces were like the faces of lions, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10729D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10729D\"></sup><i>they were</i> as swift as the gazelles on the mountains.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Ezer <i>was</i> the first, Obadiah the second, Eliab the third,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Mishmannah the fourth, Jeremiah the fifth,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Attai the sixth, Eliel the seventh,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Johanan the eighth, Elzabad the ninth,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Jeremiah the tenth, Machbannai the eleventh.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>These of the sons of Gad were captains of the army; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10735E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10735E\"></sup>he who was least was equal to a hundred and the greatest to a thousand.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10736F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10736F\"></sup>These are the ones who crossed the Jordan in the first month when it was overflowing all its banks and they put to flight all those in the valleys, both to the east and to the west.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then some of the sons of Benjamin and Judah came to the stronghold to David.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>David went out to meet them, and said to them, “If you come peacefully to me to help me, my heart shall be united with you; but if to betray me to my adversaries, since there is no wrong in my hands, may the God of our fathers look on <i>it</i> and decide.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10739G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10739G\"></sup>the Spirit came upon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10739H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10739H\"></sup>Amasai, who was the chief of the thirty, <i>and he said</i>,“<i>We</i> are yours, O David,And with you, O son of Jesse!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10739I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10739I\"></sup>Peace, peace to you,And peace to him who helps you;Indeed, your God helps you!”Then David received them and made them captains of the band.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10740J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10740J\"></sup>From Manasseh also some defected to David when he was about to go to battle with the Philistines against Saul. But they did not help them, for the lords of the Philistines after consultation sent him away, saying, “At <i>the cost of</i> our heads he may defect to his master Saul.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>As he went to Ziklag there defected to him from Manasseh: Adnah, Jozabad, Jediael, Michael, Jozabad, Elihu and Zillethai, captains of thousands who belonged to Manasseh.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They helped David against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10742K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10742K\"></sup>the band of raiders, for they were all mighty men of valor, and were captains in the army.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For day by day <i>men</i> came to David to help him, until there was a great army <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10743L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10743L\"></sup>like the army of God.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now these are the numbers of the divisions equipped for war, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10744M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10744M\"></sup>who came to David at Hebron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10744N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10744N\"></sup>to turn the kingdom of Saul to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10744O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10744O\"></sup>according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The sons of Judah who bore shield and spear <i>were</i> 6,800, equipped for war.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Of the sons of Simeon, mighty men of valor for war, 7,100.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Of the sons of Levi 4,600.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now Jehoiada was the leader of <i>the house of</i> Aaron, and with him were 3,700,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10749P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10749P\"></sup>Zadok, a young man mighty of valor, and of his father’s house twenty-two captains.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Of the sons of Benjamin, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10750Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10750Q\"></sup>Saul’s kinsmen, 3,000; for until now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10750R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10750R\"></sup>the greatest part of them had kept their allegiance to the house of Saul.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Of the sons of Ephraim 20,800, mighty men of valor, famous men in their fathers’ households.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Of the half-tribe of Manasseh 18,000, who were designated by name to come and make David king.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Of the sons of Issachar, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10753S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10753S\"></sup>men who understood the times, with knowledge of what Israel should do, their chiefs <i>were</i> two hundred; and all their kinsmen <i>were</i> at their command.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Of Zebulun, there were 50,000 who went out in the army, who could draw up in battle formation with all kinds of weapons of war and helped <i>David</i> with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10754T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10754T\"></sup>an undivided heart.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Of Naphtali <i>there were</i> 1,000 captains, and with them 37,000 with shield and spear.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Of the Danites who could draw up in battle formation, <i>there were</i> 28,600.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Of Asher <i>there were</i> 40,000 who went out in the army to draw up in battle formation.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>From the other side of the Jordan, of the Reubenites and the Gadites and of the half-tribe of Manasseh, <i>there were</i> 120,000 with all <i>kinds</i> of weapons of war for the battle.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>All these, being men of war who could draw up in battle formation, came to Hebron with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10759U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10759U\"></sup>a perfect heart to make David king over all Israel; and all the rest also of Israel were of one mind to make David king.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>They were there with David three days, eating and drinking, for their kinsmen had prepared for them.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Moreover those who were near to them, <i>even</i> as far as Issachar and Zebulun and Naphtali, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10761V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10761V\"></sup>brought food on donkeys, camels, mules and on oxen, great quantities of flour cakes, fig cakes and bunches of raisins, wine, oil, oxen and sheep. There was joy indeed in Israel."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>Then David consulted with the captains of the thousands and the hundreds, even with every leader.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>David said to all the assembly of Israel, “If it seems good to you, and if it is from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, let us send everywhere to our kinsmen who remain in all the land of Israel, also to the priests and Levites who are with them in their cities with pasture lands, that they may meet with us;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and let us bring back the ark of our God to us, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10764A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10764A\"></sup>for we did not seek it in the days of Saul.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then all the assembly said that they would do so, for the thing was right in the eyes of all the people.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10766B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10766B\"></sup>So David assembled all Israel together, from the Shihor of Egypt even to the entrance of Hamath, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10766C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10766C\"></sup>to bring the ark of God from Kiriath-jearim.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10767D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10767D\"></sup>David and all Israel went up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10767E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10767E\"></sup>Baalah, <i>that is</i>, to Kiriath-jearim, which belongs to Judah, to bring up from there the ark of God, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10767F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10767F\"></sup>who is enthroned <i>above</i> the cherubim, where His name is called.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They carried the ark of God on a new cart from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10768G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10768G\"></sup>the house of Abinadab, and Uzza and Ahio drove the cart.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>David and all Israel were celebrating before God with all <i>their</i> might, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10769H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10769H\"></sup>even with songs and with lyres, harps, tambourines, cymbals and with trumpets.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When they came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10770I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10770I\"></sup>the threshing floor of Chidon, Uzza put out his hand to hold the ark, because the oxen nearly upset <i>it</i>.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> burned against Uzza, so He struck him down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10771J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10771J\"></sup>because he put out his hand to the ark; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10771K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10771K\"></sup>and he died there before God.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then David became angry because of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> outburst against Uzza; and he called that place Perez-uzza to this day.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>David was afraid of God that day, saying, “How can I bring the ark of God <i>home</i> to me?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So David did not take the ark with him to the city of David, but took it aside <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10774L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10774L\"></sup>to the house of Obed-edom the Gittite.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Thus the ark of God remained with the family of Obed-edom in his house three months; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10775M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10775M\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> blessed the family of Obed-edom with all that he had."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10776A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10776A\"></sup>Now Hiram king of Tyre sent messengers to David with cedar trees, masons and carpenters, to build a house for him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And David realized that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had established him as king over Israel, <i>and</i> that his kingdom was highly exalted, for the sake of His people Israel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then David took more wives at Jerusalem, and David became the father of more sons and daughters.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10779B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10779B\"></sup>These are the names of the children born <i>to him</i> in Jerusalem: Shammua, Shobab, Nathan, Solomon,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Ibhar, Elishua, Elpelet,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Nogah, Nepheg, Japhia,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Elishama, Beeliada and Eliphelet.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When the Philistines heard that David had been anointed king over all Israel, all the Philistines went up in search of David; and David heard of it and went out against them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now the Philistines had come and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10784C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10784C\"></sup>made a raid in the valley of Rephaim.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>David inquired of God, saying, “Shall I go up against the Philistines? And will You give them into my hand?” Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Go up, for I will give them into your hand.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So they came up to Baal-perazim, and David defeated them there; and David said, “God has broken through my enemies by my hand, like the breakthrough of waters.” Therefore they named that place Baal-perazim.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They abandoned their gods there; so David gave the order and they were burned with fire.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The Philistines made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10788D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10788D\"></sup>yet another raid in the valley.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>David inquired again of God, and God said to him, “You shall not go up after them; circle around behind them and come at them in front of the balsam trees.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>It shall be when you hear the sound of marching in the tops of the balsam trees, then you shall go out to battle, for God will have gone out before you to strike the army of the Philistines.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>David did just as God had commanded him, and they struck down the army of the Philistines from Gibeon even as far as Gezer.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then the fame of David went out into all the lands; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10792E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10792E\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought the fear of him on all the nations."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>Now <i>David</i> built houses for himself in the city of David; and he prepared a place for the ark of God and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10793A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10793A\"></sup>pitched a tent for it.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then David said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10794B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10794B\"></sup>No one is to carry the ark of God but the Levites; for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> chose them to carry the ark of God and to minister to Him forever.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10795C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10795C\"></sup>David assembled all Israel at Jerusalem to bring up the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10795D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10795D\"></sup>to its place which he had prepared for it.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>David gathered together the sons of Aaron and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10796E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10796E\"></sup>the Levites:",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>of the sons of Kohath, Uriel the chief, and 120 of his relatives;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>of the sons of Merari, Asaiah the chief, and 220 of his relatives;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>of the sons of Gershom, Joel the chief, and 130 of his relatives;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>of the sons of Elizaphan, Shemaiah the chief, and 200 of his relatives;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>of the sons of Hebron, Eliel the chief, and 80 of his relatives;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>of the sons of Uzziel, Amminadab the chief, and 112 of his relatives.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then David called for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10803F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10803F\"></sup>Zadok and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10803G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10803G\"></sup>Abiathar the priests, and for the Levites, for Uriel, Asaiah, Joel, Shemaiah, Eliel and Amminadab,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and said to them, “You are the heads of the fathers’ <i>households</i> of the Levites; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10804H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10804H\"></sup>consecrate yourselves both you and your relatives, that you may bring up the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10804I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10804I\"></sup>to <i>the place</i> that I have prepared for it.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10805J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10805J\"></sup>Because you did not <i>carry it</i> at the first, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God made an outburst on us, for we did not seek Him according to the ordinance.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10806K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10806K\"></sup>So the priests and the Levites consecrated themselves to bring up the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10807L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10807L\"></sup>the Levites carried the ark of God on their shoulders with the poles thereon, as Moses had commanded according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then David spoke to the chiefs of the Levites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10808M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10808M\"></sup>to appoint their relatives the singers, with instruments of music, harps, lyres, loud-sounding cymbals, to raise sounds of joy.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10809N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10809N\"></sup>the Levites appointed Heman the son of Joel, and from his relatives, Asaph the son of Berechiah; and from the sons of Merari their relatives, Ethan the son of Kushaiah,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and with them their relatives of the second rank, Zechariah, Ben, Jaaziel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Unni, Eliab, Benaiah, Maaseiah, Mattithiah, Eliphelehu, Mikneiah, Obed-edom and Jeiel, the gatekeepers.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So the singers, Heman, Asaph and Ethan <i>were appointed</i> to sound aloud cymbals of bronze;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and Zechariah, Aziel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Unni, Eliab, Maaseiah and Benaiah, with harps <i>tuned</i> to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10812O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10812O\"></sup>alamoth;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and Mattithiah, Eliphelehu, Mikneiah, Obed-edom, Jeiel and Azaziah, to lead with lyres tuned to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10813P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10813P\"></sup>the sheminith.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Chenaniah, chief of the Levites, was <i>in charge of</i> the singing; he gave instruction in singing because he was skillful.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Berechiah and Elkanah were gatekeepers for the ark.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Shebaniah, Joshaphat, Nethanel, Amasai, Zechariah, Benaiah and Eliezer, the priests, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10816Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10816Q\"></sup>blew the trumpets before the ark of God. Obed-edom and Jehiah also <i>were</i> gatekeepers for the ark.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10817R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10817R\"></sup>So <i>it was</i> David, with the elders of Israel and the captains over thousands, who went to bring up the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10817S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10817S\"></sup>the house of Obed-edom with joy.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Because God was helping the Levites who were carrying the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, they sacrificed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10818T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10818T\"></sup>seven bulls and seven rams.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now David was clothed with a robe of fine linen with all the Levites who were carrying the ark, and the singers and Chenaniah the leader of the singing <i>with</i> the singers. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10819U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10819U\"></sup>David also wore an ephod of linen.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Thus all Israel brought up the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with shouting, and with sound of the horn, with trumpets, with loud-sounding cymbals, with harps and lyres.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>It happened when the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to the city of David, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10821V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10821V\"></sup>Michal the daughter of Saul looked out of the window and saw King David leaping and celebrating; and she despised him in her heart."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>And they brought in the ark of God and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10822A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10822A\"></sup>placed it inside the tent which David had pitched for it, and they offered burnt offerings and peace offerings before God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When David had finished offering the burnt offering and the peace offerings, he blessed the people in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He distributed to everyone of Israel, both man and woman, to everyone a loaf of bread and a portion <i>of meat</i> and a raisin cake.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He appointed some of the Levites <i>as</i> ministers before the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, even to celebrate and to thank and praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel:",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Asaph the chief, and second to him Zechariah, <i>then</i> Jeiel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Mattithiah, Eliab, Benaiah, Obed-edom and Jeiel, with musical instruments, harps, lyres; also Asaph <i>played</i> loud-sounding cymbals,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and Benaiah and Jahaziel the priests <i>blew</i> trumpets continually before the ark of the covenant of God.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then on that day David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10828B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10828B\"></sup>first assigned Asaph and his relatives to give thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10829C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10829C\"></sup>Oh give thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, call upon His name;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10829D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10829D\"></sup>Make known His deeds among the peoples.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Sing to Him, sing praises to Him;Speak of all His wonders.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Glory in His holy name;Let the heart of those who seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be glad.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10832E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10832E\"></sup>Seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and His strength;Seek His face continually.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10833F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10833F\"></sup>Remember His wonderful deeds which He has done,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10833G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10833G\"></sup>His marvels and the judgments from His mouth,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>O seed of Israel His servant,Sons of Jacob, His chosen ones!",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10835H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10835H\"></sup>His judgments are in all the earth.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Remember His covenant forever,The word which He commanded to a thousand generations,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10837I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10837I\"></sup><i>The covenant</i> which He made with Abraham,And His oath to Isaac.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10838J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10838J\"></sup>He also confirmed it to Jacob for a statute,To Israel as an everlasting covenant,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10839K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10839K\"></sup>To you I will give the land of Canaan,As the portion of your inheritance.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10840L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10840L\"></sup>When they were only a few in number,Very few, and strangers in it,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And they wandered about from nation to nation,And from <i>one</i> kingdom to another people,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He permitted no man to oppress them,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10842M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10842M\"></sup>He reproved kings for their sakes, <i>saying</i>,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“Do not touch My anointed ones,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10843N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10843N\"></sup>do My prophets no harm.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10844O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10844O\"></sup>Sing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, all the earth;Proclaim good tidings of His salvation from day to day.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Tell of His glory among the nations,His wonderful deeds among all the peoples.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10846P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10846P\"></sup>great is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and greatly to be praised;He also is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10846Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10846Q\"></sup>to be feared above all gods.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>For all the gods of the peoples are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10847R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10847R\"></sup>idols,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10847S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10847S\"></sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made the heavens.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Splendor and majesty are before Him,Strength and joy are in His place.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Ascribe to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, O families of the peoples,Ascribe to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> glory and strength.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Ascribe to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the glory due His name;Bring an offering, and come before Him;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10850T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10850T\"></sup>Worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in holy array.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Tremble before Him, all the earth;Indeed, the world is firmly established, it will not be moved.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10852U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10852U\"></sup>Let the heavens be glad, and let the earth rejoice;And let them say among the nations, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10852V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10852V\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> reigns.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10853W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10853W\"></sup>Let the sea roar, and all it contains;Let the field exult, and all that is in it.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then the trees of the forest will sing for joy before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;For He is coming to judge the earth.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10855X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10855X\"></sup>O give thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for <i>He is</i> good;For His lovingkindness is everlasting.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10856Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10856Y\"></sup>Then say, “Save us, O God of our salvation,And gather us and deliver us from the nations,To give thanks to Your holy name,And glory in Your praise.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10857Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10857Z\"></sup>Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel,From everlasting even to everlasting.Then all the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10857AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10857AA\"></sup>said, “Amen,” and praised the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>So he left Asaph and his relatives there <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10858AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10858AB\"></sup>before the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to minister before the ark continually, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10858AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10858AC\"></sup>as every day’s work required;",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10859AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10859AD\"></sup>Obed-edom with his 68 relatives; Obed-edom, also the son of Jeduthun, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10859AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10859AE\"></sup>Hosah as gatekeepers.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><i>He left</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10860AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10860AF\"></sup>Zadok the priest and his relatives the priests <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10860AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10860AG\"></sup>before the tabernacle of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the high place which <i>was</i> at Gibeon,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>to offer burnt offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on the altar of burnt offering continually morning and evening, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10861AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10861AH\"></sup>even according to all that is written in the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which He commanded Israel.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>With them <i>were</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10862AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10862AI\"></sup>Heman and Jeduthun, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10862AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10862AJ\"></sup>the rest who were chosen, who were designated by name, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10862AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10862AK\"></sup>give thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, because His lovingkindness is everlasting.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>And with them <i>were</i> Heman and Jeduthun <i>with</i> trumpets and cymbals for those who should sound aloud, and <i>with</i> instruments <i>for</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10863AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10863AL\"></sup>the songs of God, and the sons of Jeduthun for the gate.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10864AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10864AM\"></sup>Then all the people departed each to his house, and David returned to bless his household."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10865A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10865A\"></sup>And it came about, when David dwelt in his house, that David said to Nathan the prophet, “Behold, I am dwelling in a house of cedar, but the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is under curtains.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then Nathan said to David, “Do all that is in your heart, for God is with you.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>It came about the same night that the word of God came to Nathan, saying,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Go and tell David My servant, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10868B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10868B\"></sup>You shall not build a house for Me to dwell in;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>for I have not dwelt in a house since the day that I brought up Israel to this day, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10869C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10869C\"></sup>but I have gone from tent to tent and from <i>one</i> dwelling place <i>to another</i>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>In all places where I have walked with all Israel, have I spoken a word <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10870D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10870D\"></sup>with any of the judges of Israel, whom I commanded to shepherd My people, saying, ‘Why have you not built for Me a house of cedar?’”’",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now, therefore, thus shall you say to My servant David, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts, “I took you from the pasture, from following the sheep, to be leader over My people Israel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I have been with you wherever you have gone, and have cut off all your enemies from before you; and I will make you a name like the name of the great ones who are in the earth.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>I will appoint a place for My people Israel, and will plant them, so that they may dwell in their own place and not be moved again; and the wicked will not waste them anymore as formerly,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>even from the day that I commanded judges <i>to be</i> over My people Israel. And I will subdue all your enemies.Moreover, I tell you that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will build a house for you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When your days are fulfilled that you must go <i>to be</i> with your fathers, that I will set up <i>one of</i> your descendants after you, who will be of your sons; and I will establish his kingdom.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He shall build for Me a house, and I will establish his throne forever.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10877E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10877E\"></sup>I will be his father and he shall be My son; and I will not take My lovingkindness away from him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10877F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10877F\"></sup>as I took it from him who was before you.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But I will settle him in My house and in My kingdom forever, and his throne shall be established forever.”’”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>According to all these words and according to all this vision, so Nathan spoke to David.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then David the king went in and sat before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10880G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10880G\"></sup>Who am I, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, and what is my house that You have brought me this far?",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>This was a small thing in Your eyes, O God; but You have spoken of Your servant’s house for a great while to come, and have regarded me according to the standard of a man of high degree, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>What more can David still <i>say</i> to You concerning the honor <i>bestowed</i> on Your servant? For You know Your servant.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10883H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10883H\"></sup>for Your servant’s sake, and according to Your own heart, You have wrought all this greatness, to make known all these great things.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, there is none like You, nor is there any God besides You, according to all that we have heard with our ears.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And what one nation in the earth is like Your people Israel, whom God went to redeem for Himself <i>as</i> a people, to make You a name by great and terrible things, in driving out nations from before Your people, whom You redeemed out of Egypt?",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10886I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10886I\"></sup>For Your people Israel You made Your own people forever, and You, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, became their God.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Now, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, let the word that You have spoken concerning Your servant and concerning his house be established forever, and do as You have spoken.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Let Your name be established and magnified forever, saying, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts is the God of Israel, <i>even</i> a God to Israel; and the house of David Your servant is established before You.’",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>For You, O my God, have revealed to Your servant that You will build for him a house; therefore Your servant has found <i>courage</i> to pray before You.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, You are God, and have promised this good thing to Your servant.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And now it has pleased You to bless the house of Your servant, that it may continue forever before You; for You, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, have blessed, and it is blessed forever.”"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>Now after this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10892A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10892A\"></sup>it came about that David defeated the Philistines and subdued them and took Gath and its towns from the hand of the Philistines.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He defeated Moab, and the Moabites became servants to David, bringing tribute.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>David also defeated Hadadezer king of Zobah <i>as far as</i> Hamath, as he went to establish his rule to the Euphrates River.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>David took from him 1,000 chariots and 7,000 horsemen and 20,000 foot soldiers, and David hamstrung all the chariot horses, but reserved <i>enough</i> of them for 100 chariots.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When the Arameans of Damascus came to help Hadadezer king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10896B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10896B\"></sup>of Zobah, David killed 22,000 men of the Arameans.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then David put <i>garrisons</i> among the Arameans of Damascus; and the Arameans became servants to David, bringing tribute. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> helped David wherever he went.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>David took the shields of gold which were carried by the servants of Hadadezer and brought them to Jerusalem.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Also from Tibhath and from Cun, cities of Hadadezer, David took a very large amount of bronze, with which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10899C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10899C\"></sup>Solomon made the bronze sea and the pillars and the bronze utensils.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now when Tou king of Hamath heard that David had defeated all the army of Hadadezer king of Zobah,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>he sent Hadoram his son to King David to greet him and to bless him, because he had fought against Hadadezer and had defeated him; for Hadadezer had been at war with Tou. And <i>Hadoram brought</i> all kinds of articles of gold and silver and bronze.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>King David also dedicated these to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with the silver and the gold which he had carried away from all the nations: from Edom, Moab, the sons of Ammon, the Philistines, and from Amalek.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Moreover Abishai the son of Zeruiah defeated 18,000 Edomites in the Valley of Salt.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then he put garrisons in Edom, and all the Edomites became servants to David. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> helped David wherever he went.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So David reigned over all Israel; and he administered justice and righteousness for all his people.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10906D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10906D\"></sup>Joab the son of Zeruiah <i>was</i> over the army, and Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud <i>was</i> recorder;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and Zadok the son of Ahitub and Abimelech the son of Abiathar <i>were</i> priests, and Shavsha <i>was</i> secretary;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada <i>was</i> over the Cherethites and the Pelethites, and the sons of David <i>were</i> chiefs at the king’s side."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10909A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10909A\"></sup>Now it came about after this, that Nahash the king of the sons of Ammon died, and his son became king in his place.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then David said, “I will show kindness to Hanun the son of Nahash, because his father showed kindness to me.” So David sent messengers to console him concerning his father. And David’s servants came into the land of the sons of Ammon to Hanun to console him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But the princes of the sons of Ammon said to Hanun, “Do you think that David is honoring your father, in that he has sent comforters to you? Have not his servants come to you to search and to overthrow and to spy out the land?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Hanun took David’s servants and shaved them and cut off their garments in the middle as far as their hips, and sent them away.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then <i>certain persons</i> went and told David about the men. And he sent to meet them, for the men were greatly humiliated. And the king said, “Stay at Jericho until your beards grow, and <i>then</i> return.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When the sons of Ammon saw that they had made themselves odious to David, Hanun and the sons of Ammon sent 1,000 talents of silver to hire for themselves chariots and horsemen from Mesopotamia, from Aram-maacah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10914B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10914B\"></sup>from Zobah.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So they hired for themselves 32,000 chariots, and the king of Maacah and his people, who came and camped before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10915C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10915C\"></sup>Medeba. And the sons of Ammon gathered together from their cities and came to battle.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When David heard <i>of it</i>, he sent Joab and all the army, the mighty men.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The sons of Ammon came out and drew up in battle array at the entrance of the city, and the kings who had come were by themselves in the field.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now when Joab saw that the battle was set against him in front and in the rear, he selected from all the choice men of Israel and they arrayed themselves against the Arameans.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But the remainder of the people he placed in the hand of Abshai his brother; and they arrayed themselves against the sons of Ammon.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He said, “If the Arameans are too strong for me, then you shall help me; but if the sons of Ammon are too strong for you, then I will help you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Be strong, and let us show ourselves courageous for the sake of our people and for the cities of our God; and may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> do what is good in His sight.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So Joab and the people who were with him drew near to the battle against the Arameans, and they fled before him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When the sons of Ammon saw that the Arameans fled, they also fled before Abshai his brother and entered the city. Then Joab came to Jerusalem.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When the Arameans saw that they had been defeated by Israel, they sent messengers and brought out the Arameans who were beyond the River, with Shophach the commander of the army of Hadadezer leading them.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When it was told David, he gathered all Israel together and crossed the Jordan, and came upon them and drew up in formation against them. And when David drew up in battle array against the Arameans, they fought against him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The Arameans fled before Israel, and David killed of the Arameans 7,000 charioteers and 40,000 foot soldiers, and put to death Shophach the commander of the army.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So when the servants of Hadadezer saw that they were defeated by Israel, they made peace with David and served him. Thus the Arameans were not willing to help the sons of Ammon anymore."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10928A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10928A\"></sup>Then it happened in the spring, at the time when kings go out <i>to battle</i>, that Joab led out the army and ravaged the land of the sons of Ammon, and came and besieged Rabbah. But David stayed at Jerusalem. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10928B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10928B\"></sup>Joab struck Rabbah and overthrew it.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10929C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10929C\"></sup>David took the crown of their king from his head, and he found it to weigh a talent of gold, and there was a precious stone in it; and it was placed on David’s head. And he brought out the spoil of the city, a very great amount.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He brought out the people who <i>were</i> in it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10930D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10930D\"></sup>and cut <i>them</i> with saws and with sharp instruments and with axes. And thus David did to all the cities of the sons of Ammon. Then David and all the people returned <i>to</i> Jerusalem.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10931E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10931E\"></sup>Now it came about after this, that war broke out at Gezer with the Philistines; then Sibbecai the Hushathite killed Sippai, one of the descendants of the giants, and they were subdued.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And there was war with the Philistines again, and Elhanan the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10932F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10932F\"></sup>Jair killed Lahmi the brother of Goliath the Gittite, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10932G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10932G\"></sup>shaft of whose spear <i>was</i> like a weaver’s beam.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Again there was war at Gath, where there was a man of <i>great</i> stature who had twenty-four fingers and toes, six <i>fingers on each hand</i> and six <i>toes on each foot</i>; and he also was descended from the giants.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When he taunted Israel, Jonathan the son of Shimea, David’s brother, killed him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>These were descended from the giants in Gath, and they fell by the hand of David and by the hand of his servants."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10936A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10936A\"></sup>Then Satan stood up against Israel and moved David to number Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So David said to Joab and to the princes of the people, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10937B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10937B\"></sup>Go, number Israel from Beersheba even to Dan, and bring me <i>word</i> that I may know their number.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Joab said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10938C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10938C\"></sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> add to His people a hundred times as many as they are! But, my lord the king, are they not all my lord’s servants? Why does my lord seek this thing? Why should he be a cause of guilt to Israel?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Nevertheless, the king’s word prevailed against Joab. Therefore, Joab departed and went throughout all Israel, and came to Jerusalem.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Joab gave the number of the census of <i>all</i> the people to David. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10940D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10940D\"></sup>all Israel were 1,100,000 men who drew the sword; and Judah <i>was</i> 470,000 men who drew the sword.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10941E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10941E\"></sup>But he did not number Levi and Benjamin among them, for the king’s command was abhorrent to Joab.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>God was displeased with this thing, so He struck Israel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>David said to God, “I have sinned greatly, in that I have done this thing. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10943F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10943F\"></sup>But now, please take away the iniquity of Your servant, for I have done very foolishly.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10944G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10944G\"></sup>Gad, David’s <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10944H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10944H\"></sup>seer, saying,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Go and speak to David, saying, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “I offer you three things; choose for yourself one of them, which I will do to you.”’”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Gad came to David and said to him, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘Take for yourself",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10947I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10947I\"></sup>either three years of famine, or three months to be swept away before your foes, while the sword of your enemies overtakes <i>you</i>, or else three days of the sword of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, even pestilence in the land, and the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> destroying throughout all the territory of Israel.’ Now, therefore, consider what answer I shall return to Him who sent me.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>David said to Gad, “I am in great distress; please let me fall into the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10948J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10948J\"></sup>for His mercies are very great. But do not let me fall into the hand of man.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10949K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10949K\"></sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent a pestilence on Israel; 70,000 men of Israel fell.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And God sent an angel to Jerusalem to destroy it; but as he was about to destroy <i>it</i>, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saw and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10950L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10950L\"></sup>was sorry over the calamity, and said to the destroying angel, “It is enough; now relax your hand.” And the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was standing by the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then David lifted up his eyes and saw the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> standing between earth and heaven, with his drawn sword in his hand stretched out over Jerusalem. Then David and the elders, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10951M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10951M\"></sup>covered with sackcloth, fell on their faces.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>David said to God, “Is it not I who commanded to count the people? Indeed, I am the one who has sinned and done very wickedly, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10952N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10952N\"></sup>but these sheep, what have they done? O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, please let Your hand be against me and my father’s household, but not against Your people that they should be plagued.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10953O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10953O\"></sup>Then the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Gad to say to David, that David should go up and build an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So David went up at the word of Gad, which he spoke in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now Ornan turned back and saw the angel, and his four sons <i>who were</i> with him hid themselves. And Ornan was threshing wheat.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>As David came to Ornan, Ornan looked and saw David, and went out from the threshing floor and prostrated himself before David with his face to the ground.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then David said to Ornan, “Give me the site of <i>this</i> threshing floor, that I may build on it an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; for the full price you shall give it to me, that the plague may be restrained from the people.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Ornan said to David, “Take <i>it</i> for yourself; and let my lord the king do what is good in his sight. See, I will give the oxen for burnt offerings and the threshing sledges for wood and the wheat for the grain offering; I will give <i>it</i> all.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But King David said to Ornan, “No, but I will surely buy <i>it</i> for the full price; for I will not take what is yours for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, or offer a burnt offering which costs me nothing.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10960P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10960P\"></sup>David gave Ornan 600 shekels of gold by weight for the site.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then David built an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> there and offered burnt offerings and peace offerings. And he called to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10961Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10961Q\"></sup>He answered him with fire from heaven on the altar of burnt offering.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded the angel, and he put his sword back in its sheath.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>At that time, when David saw that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had answered him on the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite, he offered sacrifice there.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10964R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10964R\"></sup>For the tabernacle of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which Moses had made in the wilderness, and the altar of burnt offering <i>were</i> in the high place at Gibeon at that time.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But David could not go before it to inquire of God, for he was terrified by the sword of the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>Then David said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10966A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10966A\"></sup>This is the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, and this is the altar of burnt offering for Israel.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So David gave orders to gather <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10967B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10967B\"></sup>the foreigners who were in the land of Israel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10967C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10967C\"></sup>he set stonecutters to hew out stones to build the house of God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10968D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10968D\"></sup>prepared large quantities of iron to make the nails for the doors of the gates and for the clamps, and more <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10968E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10968E\"></sup>bronze than could be weighed;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and timbers of cedar logs beyond number, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10969F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10969F\"></sup>the Sidonians and Tyrians brought large quantities of cedar timber to David.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>David said, “My son <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10970G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10970G\"></sup>Solomon is young and inexperienced, and the house that is to be built for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shall be exceedingly magnificent, famous and glorious throughout all lands. <i>Therefore</i> now I will make preparation for it.” So David made ample preparations before his death.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10971H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10971H\"></sup>he called for his son Solomon, and charged him to build a house for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>David said to Solomon, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10972I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10972I\"></sup>My son, I had intended to build a house to the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to me, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10973J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10973J\"></sup>You have shed much blood and have waged great wars; you shall not build a house to My name, because you have shed <i>so</i> much blood on the earth before Me.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Behold, a son will be born to you, who shall be a man of rest; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10974K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10974K\"></sup>I will give him rest from all his enemies on every side; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10974L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10974L\"></sup>his name shall be Solomon, and I will give peace and quiet to Israel in his days.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10975M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10975M\"></sup>He shall build a house for My name, and he shall be My son and I will be his father; and I will establish the throne of his kingdom over Israel forever.’",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now, my son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10976N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10976N\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be with you that you may be successful, and build the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God just as He has spoken concerning you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10977O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10977O\"></sup>Only the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> give you discretion and understanding, and give you charge over Israel, so that you may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10977P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10977P\"></sup>keep the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10978Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10978Q\"></sup>Then you will prosper, if you are careful to observe the statutes and the ordinances which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses concerning Israel. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10978R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10978R\"></sup>Be strong and courageous, do not fear nor be dismayed.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now behold, with great pains I have prepared for the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10979S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10979S\"></sup>100,000 talents of gold and 1,000,000 talents of silver, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10979T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10979T\"></sup>bronze and iron beyond weight, for they are in great quantity; also timber and stone I have prepared, and you may add to them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Moreover, there are many workmen with you, stonecutters and masons of stone and carpenters, and all men who are skillful in every kind of work.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Of the gold, the silver and the bronze and the iron there is no limit. Arise and work, and may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10981U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10981U\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be with you.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10982V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10982V\"></sup>David also commanded all the leaders of Israel to help his son Solomon, <i>saying</i>,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Is not the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God with you? And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10983W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10983W\"></sup>has He not given you rest on every side? For He has given the inhabitants of the land into my hand, and the land is subdued before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and before His people.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10984X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10984X\"></sup>set your heart and your soul to seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God; arise, therefore, and build the sanctuary of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10984Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10984Y\"></sup>so that you may bring the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the holy vessels of God into the house that is to be built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10984Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10984Z\"></sup>for the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”"
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10985A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10985A\"></sup>Now when David reached old age, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10985B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10985B\"></sup>he made his son Solomon king over Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he gathered together all the leaders of Israel with the priests and the Levites.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10987C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10987C\"></sup>The Levites were numbered from thirty years old and upward, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10987D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10987D\"></sup>their number by census of men was 38,000.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Of these, 24,000 were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10988E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10988E\"></sup>to oversee the work of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and 6,000 <i>were</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10988F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10988F\"></sup>officers and judges,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and 4,000 <i>were</i> gatekeepers, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10989G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10989G\"></sup>4,000 <i>were</i> praising the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with the instruments which David made for giving praise.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>David divided them into divisions <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10990H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10990H\"></sup>according to the sons of Levi: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Of the Gershonites <i>were</i> Ladan and Shimei.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The sons of Ladan <i>were</i> Jehiel the first and Zetham and Joel, three.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The sons of Shimei <i>were</i> Shelomoth and Haziel and Haran, three. These were the heads of the fathers’ <i>households</i> of Ladan.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The sons of Shimei <i>were</i> Jahath, Zina, Jeush and Beriah. These four <i>were</i> the sons of Shimei.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Jahath was the first and Zizah the second; but Jeush and Beriah did not have many sons, so they became a father’s household, one class.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The sons of Kohath were four: Amram, Izhar, Hebron and Uzziel.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10997I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10997I\"></sup>The sons of Amram were Aaron and Moses. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10997J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10997J\"></sup>Aaron was set apart to sanctify him as most holy, he and his sons forever, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10997K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10997K\"></sup>to burn incense before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to minister to Him and to bless in His name forever.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But <i>as for</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10998L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10998L\"></sup>Moses the man of God, his sons were named among the tribe of Levi.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The sons of Moses <i>were</i> Gershom and Eliezer.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The son of Gershom <i>was</i> Shebuel the chief.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The son of Eliezer was Rehabiah the chief; and Eliezer had no other sons, but the sons of Rehabiah were very many.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The son of Izhar was Shelomith the chief.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The sons of Hebron <i>were</i> Jeriah the first, Amariah the second, Jahaziel the third and Jekameam the fourth.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The sons of Uzziel <i>were</i> Micah the first and Isshiah the second.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The sons of Merari were Mahli and Mushi. The sons of Mahli <i>were</i> Eleazar and Kish.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Eleazar died and had no sons, but daughters only, so their brothers, the sons of Kish, took them <i>as wives</i>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The sons of Mushi <i>were</i> three: Mahli, Eder and Jeremoth.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11008M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11008M\"></sup>These were the sons of Levi according to their fathers’ households, <i>even</i> the heads of the fathers’ <i>households</i> of those of them who were counted, in the number of names by their census, doing the work for the service of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11008N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11008N\"></sup>from twenty years old and upward.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>For David said, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11009O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11009O\"></sup>has given rest to His people, and He dwells in Jerusalem forever.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Also, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11010P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11010P\"></sup>the Levites will no longer need to carry the tabernacle and all its utensils for its service.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>For by the last words of David the sons of Levi <i>were</i> numbered from twenty years old and upward.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>For their office is to assist the sons of Aaron with the service of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, in the courts and in the chambers and in the purifying of all holy things, even the work of the service of the house of God,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11013Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11013Q\"></sup>and with the showbread, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11013R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11013R\"></sup>the fine flour for a grain offering, and unleavened wafers, or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11013S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11013S\"></sup><i>what is baked in</i> the pan or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11013T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11013T\"></sup>what is well-mixed, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11013U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11013U\"></sup>all measures of volume and size.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>They are to stand every morning to thank and to praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and likewise at evening,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and to offer all burnt offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11015V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11015V\"></sup>on the sabbaths, the new moons and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11015W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11015W\"></sup>the fixed festivals in the number <i>set</i> by the ordinance concerning them, continually before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11016X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11016X\"></sup>they are to keep charge of the tent of meeting, and charge of the holy place, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11016Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11016Y\"></sup>charge of the sons of Aaron their relatives, for the service of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>Now the divisions of the descendants of Aaron <i>were these</i>: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11017A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11017A\"></sup>the sons of Aaron <i>were</i> Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar and Ithamar.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11018B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11018B\"></sup>But Nadab and Abihu died before their father and had no sons. So Eleazar and Ithamar served as priests.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>David, with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11019C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11019C\"></sup>Zadok of the sons of Eleazar and Ahimelech of the sons of Ithamar, divided them according to their offices for their ministry.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Since more chief men were found from the descendants of Eleazar than the descendants of Ithamar, they divided them thus: <i>there were</i> sixteen heads of fathers’ households of the descendants of Eleazar and eight of the descendants of Ithamar, according to their fathers’ households.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11021D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11021D\"></sup>Thus they were divided by lot, the one as the other; for they were officers of the sanctuary and officers of God, both from the descendants of Eleazar and the descendants of Ithamar.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Shemaiah, the son of Nethanel the scribe, from the Levites, recorded them in the presence of the king, the princes, Zadok the priest, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11022E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11022E\"></sup>Ahimelech the son of Abiathar, and the heads of the fathers’ <i>households</i> of the priests and of the Levites; one father’s household taken for Eleazar and one taken for Ithamar.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now the first lot came out for Jehoiarib, the second for Jedaiah,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>the third for Harim, the fourth for Seorim,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>the fifth for Malchijah, the sixth for Mijamin,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>the seventh for Hakkoz, the eighth for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11026F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11026F\"></sup>Abijah,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>the ninth for Jeshua, the tenth for Shecaniah,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>the eleventh for Eliashib, the twelfth for Jakim,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>the thirteenth for Huppah, the fourteenth for Jeshebeab,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>the fifteenth for Bilgah, the sixteenth for Immer,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>the seventeenth for Hezir, the eighteenth for Happizzez,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the nineteenth for Pethahiah, the twentieth for Jehezkel,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>the twenty-first for Jachin, the twenty-second for Gamul,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>the twenty-third for Delaiah, the twenty-fourth for Maaziah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11035G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11035G\"></sup>These were their offices for their ministry when <i>they</i> came in to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> according to the ordinance <i>given</i> to them through Aaron their father, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel had commanded him.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now for the rest of the sons of Levi: of the sons of Amram, Shubael; of the sons of Shubael, Jehdeiah.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Of Rehabiah: of the sons of Rehabiah, Isshiah the first.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Of the Izharites, Shelomoth; of the sons of Shelomoth, Jahath.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The sons <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11039H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11039H\"></sup><i>of Hebron</i>: Jeriah <i>the first</i>, Amariah the second, Jahaziel the third, Jekameam the fourth.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><i>Of</i> the sons of Uzziel, Micah; of the sons of Micah, Shamir.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The brother of Micah, Isshiah; of the sons of Isshiah, Zechariah.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The sons of Merari, Mahli and Mushi; the sons of Jaaziah, Beno.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The sons of Merari: by Jaaziah <i>were</i> Beno, Shoham, Zaccur and Ibri.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>By Mahli: Eleazar, who had no sons.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>By Kish: the sons of Kish, Jerahmeel.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The sons of Mushi: Mahli, Eder and Jerimoth. These <i>were</i> the sons of the Levites according to their fathers’ households.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11047I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11047I\"></sup>These also cast lots just as their relatives the sons of Aaron in the presence of David the king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11047J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11047J\"></sup>Zadok, Ahimelech, and the heads of the fathers’ <i>households</i> of the priests and of the Levites—the head of fathers’ <i>households</i> as well as those of his younger brother."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span>Moreover, David and the commanders of the army set apart for the service <i>some</i> of the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11048A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11048A\"></sup>Asaph and of Heman and of Jeduthun, who <i>were</i> to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11048B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11048B\"></sup>prophesy with lyres, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11048C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11048C\"></sup>harps and cymbals; and the number of those who performed their service was:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Of the sons of Asaph: Zaccur, Joseph, Nethaniah and Asharelah; the sons of Asaph <i>were</i> under the direction of Asaph, who prophesied under the direction of the king.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11050D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11050D\"></sup>Of Jeduthun, the sons of Jeduthun: Gedaliah, Zeri, Jeshaiah, Shimei, Hashabiah and Mattithiah, six, under the direction of their father Jeduthun with the harp, who prophesied in giving thanks and praising the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Of Heman, the sons of Heman: Bukkiah, Mattaniah, Uzziel, Shebuel and Jerimoth, Hananiah, Hanani, Eliathah, Giddalti and Romamti-ezer, Joshbekashah, Mallothi, Hothir, Mahazioth.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>All these <i>were</i> the sons of Heman <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11052E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11052E\"></sup>the king’s seer to exalt him according to the words of God, for God gave fourteen sons and three daughters to Heman.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>All these were under the direction of their father to sing in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11053F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11053F\"></sup>with cymbals, harps and lyres, for the service of the house of God. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11053G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11053G\"></sup>Asaph, Jeduthun and Heman <i>were</i> under the direction of the king.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Their number who were trained in singing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, with their relatives, all who were skillful, <i>was</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11054H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11054H\"></sup>288.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11055I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11055I\"></sup>They cast lots for their duties, all alike, the small as well as the great, the teacher <i>as well</i> as the pupil.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now the first lot came out for Asaph to Joseph, the second for Gedaliah, he with his relatives and sons <i>were</i> twelve;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>the third to Zaccur, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>the fourth to Izri, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>the fifth to Nethaniah, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>the sixth to Bukkiah, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>the seventh to Jesharelah, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>the eighth to Jeshaiah, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the ninth to Mattaniah, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>the tenth to Shimei, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>the eleventh to Azarel, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>the twelfth to Hashabiah, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>for the thirteenth, Shubael, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>for the fourteenth, Mattithiah, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>for the fifteenth to Jeremoth, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>for the sixteenth to Hananiah, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>for the seventeenth to Joshbekashah, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>for the eighteenth to Hanani, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>for the nineteenth to Mallothi, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>for the twentieth to Eliathah, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>for the twenty-first to Hothir, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>for the twenty-second to Giddalti, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>for the twenty-third to Mahazioth, his sons and his relatives, twelve;",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>for the twenty-fourth to Romamti-ezer, his sons and his relatives, twelve."
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span>For the divisions of the gatekeepers <i>there were</i> of the Korahites, Meshelemiah the son of Kore, of the sons of Asaph.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Meshelemiah had sons: Zechariah the firstborn, Jediael the second, Zebadiah the third, Jathniel the fourth,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Elam the fifth, Johanan the sixth, Eliehoenai the seventh.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11082A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11082A\"></sup>Obed-edom had sons: Shemaiah the firstborn, Jehozabad the second, Joah the third, Sacar the fourth, Nethanel the fifth,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Ammiel the sixth, Issachar the seventh <i>and</i> Peullethai the eighth; God had indeed blessed him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Also to his son Shemaiah sons were born who ruled over the house of their father, for they were mighty men of valor.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The sons of Shemaiah <i>were</i> Othni, Rephael, Obed and Elzabad, whose brothers, Elihu and Semachiah, were valiant men.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>All these <i>were</i> of the sons of Obed-edom; they and their sons and their relatives <i>were</i> able men with strength for the service, 62 from Obed-edom.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Meshelemiah had sons and relatives, 18 valiant men.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11088B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11088B\"></sup>Hosah, <i>one</i> of the sons of Merari had sons: Shimri the first (although he was not the firstborn, his father made him first),",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Hilkiah the second, Tebaliah the third, Zechariah the fourth; all the sons and relatives of Hosah <i>were</i> 13.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>To these divisions of the gatekeepers, the chief men, <i>were given</i> duties like their relatives to minister in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11091C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11091C\"></sup>They cast lots, the small and the great alike, according to their fathers’ households, for every gate.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The lot to the east fell to Shelemiah. Then they cast lots <i>for</i> his son Zechariah, a counselor with insight, and his lot came out to the north.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>For Obed-edom <i>it fell</i> to the south, and to his sons went the storehouse.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For Shuppim and Hosah <i>it was</i> to the west, by the gate of Shallecheth, on the ascending highway. Guard corresponded to guard.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>On the east there were six Levites, on the north four daily, on the south four daily, and at the storehouse two by two.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>At the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11096D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11096D\"></sup>Parbar on the west <i>there were</i> four at the highway and two at the Parbar.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>These were the divisions of the gatekeepers of the sons of Korah and of the sons of Merari.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The Levites, their relatives, had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11098E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11098E\"></sup>charge of the treasures of the house of God and of the treasures of the dedicated gifts.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The sons of Ladan, the sons of the Gershonites belonging to Ladan, <i>namely</i>, the Jehielites, <i>were</i> the heads of the fathers’ <i>households</i>, belonging to Ladan the Gershonite.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The sons of Jehieli, Zetham and Joel his brother, had charge of the treasures of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>As for the Amramites, the Izharites, the Hebronites and the Uzzielites,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Shebuel the son of Gershom, the son of Moses, was officer over the treasures.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>His relatives by Eliezer <i>were</i> Rehabiah his son, Jeshaiah his son, Joram his son, Zichri his son and Shelomoth his son.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>This Shelomoth and his relatives had charge of all the treasures of the dedicated gifts <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11104F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11104F\"></sup>which King David and the heads of the fathers’ <i>households</i>, the commanders of thousands and hundreds, and the commanders of the army, had dedicated.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>They dedicated part of the spoil won in battles to repair the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And all that Samuel the seer had dedicated and Saul the son of Kish, Abner the son of Ner and Joab the son of Zeruiah, everyone who had dedicated <i>anything, all of this</i> was in the care of Shelomoth and his relatives.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>As for the Izharites, Chenaniah and his sons <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11107G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11107G\"></sup>were <i>assigned</i> to outside duties for Israel, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11107H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11107H\"></sup>officers and judges.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>As for the Hebronites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11108I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11108I\"></sup>Hashabiah and his relatives, 1,700 capable men, had charge of the affairs of Israel west of the Jordan, for all the work of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the service of the king.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>As for the Hebronites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11109J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11109J\"></sup>Jerijah the chief (these Hebronites were investigated according to their genealogies and fathers’ <i>households</i>, in the fortieth year of David’s reign, and men of outstanding capability were found among them at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11109K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11109K\"></sup>Jazer of Gilead)",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>and his relatives, capable men, <i>were</i> 2,700 in number, heads of fathers’ <i>households</i>. And King David made them overseers of the Reubenites, the Gadites and the half-tribe of the Manassites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11110L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11110L\"></sup>concerning all the affairs of God and of the king."
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span>Now <i>this is</i> the enumeration of the sons of Israel, the heads of fathers’ <i>households</i>, the commanders of thousands and of hundreds, and their officers who served the king in all the affairs of the divisions which came in and went out month by month throughout all the months of the year, each division <i>numbering</i> 24,000:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Jashobeam the son of Zabdiel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11112A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11112A\"></sup>had charge of the first division for the first month; and in his division <i>were</i> 24,000.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><i>He was</i> from the sons of Perez, <i>and was</i> chief of all the commanders of the army for the first month.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Dodai the Ahohite and his division had charge of the division for the second month, Mikloth <i>being</i> the chief officer; and in his division <i>were</i> 24,000.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The third commander of the army for the third month <i>was</i> Benaiah, the son of Jehoiada the priest, <i>as</i> chief; and in his division <i>were</i> 24,000.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>This Benaiah <i>was</i> the mighty man of the thirty, and had charge of thirty; and over his division was Ammizabad his son.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The fourth for the fourth month <i>was</i> Asahel the brother of Joab, and Zebadiah his son after him; and in his division <i>were</i> 24,000.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The fifth for the fifth month <i>was</i> the commander Shamhuth the Izrahite; and in his division <i>were</i> 24,000.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The sixth for the sixth month <i>was</i> Ira the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite; and in his division <i>were</i> 24,000.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The seventh for the seventh month <i>was</i> Helez the Pelonite of the sons of Ephraim; and in his division <i>were</i> 24,000.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The eighth for the eighth month <i>was</i> Sibbecai the Hushathite of the Zerahites; and in his division <i>were</i> 24,000.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The ninth for the ninth month <i>was</i> Abiezer the Anathothite of the Benjamites; and in his division <i>were</i> 24,000.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The tenth for the tenth month <i>was</i> Maharai the Netophathite of the Zerahites; and in his division <i>were</i> 24,000.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The eleventh for the eleventh month <i>was</i> Benaiah the Pirathonite of the sons of Ephraim; and in his division <i>were</i> 24,000.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The twelfth for the twelfth month <i>was</i> Heldai the Netophathite of Othniel; and in his division <i>were</i> 24,000.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now in charge of the tribes of Israel: chief officer for the Reubenites was Eliezer the son of Zichri; for the Simeonites, Shephatiah the son of Maacah;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>for Levi, Hashabiah the son of Kemuel; for Aaron, Zadok;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>for Judah, Elihu, <i>one</i> of David’s brothers; for Issachar, Omri the son of Michael;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>for Zebulun, Ishmaiah the son of Obadiah; for Naphtali, Jeremoth the son of Azriel;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>for the sons of Ephraim, Hoshea the son of Azaziah; for the half-tribe of Manasseh, Joel the son of Pedaiah;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>for the half-tribe of Manasseh in Gilead, Iddo the son of Zechariah; for Benjamin, Jaasiel the son of Abner;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>for Dan, Azarel the son of Jeroham. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11132B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11132B\"></sup>These <i>were</i> the princes of the tribes of Israel.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But David did not count those twenty years of age and under, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11133C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11133C\"></sup>because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said He would multiply Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11133D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11133D\"></sup>as the stars of heaven.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Joab the son of Zeruiah had begun to count <i>them</i>, but did not finish; and because of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11134E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11134E\"></sup>this, wrath came upon Israel, and the number was not included in the account of the chronicles of King David.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now Azmaveth the son of Adiel had charge of the king’s storehouses. And Jonathan the son of Uzziah had charge of the storehouses in the country, in the cities, in the villages and in the towers.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Ezri the son of Chelub had charge of the agricultural workers who tilled the soil.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Shimei the Ramathite had charge of the vineyards; and Zabdi the Shiphmite had charge of the produce of the vineyards <i>stored</i> in the wine cellars.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Baal-hanan the Gederite had charge of the olive and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11138F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11138F\"></sup>sycamore trees in the Shephelah; and Joash had charge of the stores of oil.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Shitrai the Sharonite had charge of the cattle which were grazing in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11139G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11139G\"></sup>Sharon; and Shaphat the son of Adlai had charge of the cattle in the valleys.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Obil the Ishmaelite had charge of the camels; and Jehdeiah the Meronothite had charge of the donkeys.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Jaziz the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11141H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11141H\"></sup>Hagrite had charge of the flocks. All these were overseers of the property which belonged to King David.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Also Jonathan, David’s uncle, <i>was</i> a counselor, a man of understanding, and a scribe; and Jehiel the son of Hachmoni tutored the king’s sons.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11143I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11143I\"></sup>Ahithophel <i>was</i> counselor to the king; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11143J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11143J\"></sup>Hushai the Archite <i>was</i> the king’s friend.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Jehoiada the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11144K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11144K\"></sup>Benaiah, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11144L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11144L\"></sup>Abiathar succeeded Ahithophel; and Joab was the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11144M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11144M\"></sup>commander of the king’s army."
		},
		"28": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">28 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11145A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11145A\"></sup>David assembled at Jerusalem all the officials of Israel, the princes of the tribes, and the commanders of the divisions that served the king, and the commanders of thousands, and the commanders of hundreds, and the overseers of all the property and livestock belonging to the king and his sons, with the officials and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11145B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11145B\"></sup>the mighty men, even all the valiant men.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then King David rose to his feet and said, “Listen to me, my brethren and my people; I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11146C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11146C\"></sup><i>had</i> intended to build a permanent home for the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11146D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11146D\"></sup>the footstool of our God. So I had made preparations to build <i>it</i>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But God said to me, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11147E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11147E\"></sup>You shall not build a house for My name because you are a man of war and have shed blood.’",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Yet, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11148F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11148F\"></sup>chose me from all the house of my father to be king over Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11148G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11148G\"></sup>forever. For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11148H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11148H\"></sup>He has chosen Judah to be a leader; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11148I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11148I\"></sup>in the house of Judah, my father’s house, and among the sons of my father He took pleasure in me to make <i>me</i> king over all Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11149J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11149J\"></sup>Of all my sons (for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given me many sons), <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11149K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11149K\"></sup>He has chosen my son Solomon to sit on the throne of the kingdom of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> over Israel.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He said to me, ‘Your son <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11150L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11150L\"></sup>Solomon is the one who shall build My house and My courts; for I have chosen him to be a son to Me, and I will be a father to him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I will establish his kingdom forever <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11151M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11151M\"></sup>if he resolutely performs My commandments and My ordinances, as is done now.’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So now, in the sight of all Israel, the assembly of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and in the hearing of our God, observe and seek after all the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God so that you may possess the good land and bequeath <i>it</i> to your sons after you forever.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“As for you, my son Solomon, know the God of your father, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11153N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11153N\"></sup>serve Him with a whole heart and a willing mind; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11153O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11153O\"></sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> searches all hearts, and understands every intent of the thoughts. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11153P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11153P\"></sup>If you seek Him, He will let you find Him; but if you forsake Him, He will reject you forever.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Consider now, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has chosen you to build a house for the sanctuary; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11154Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11154Q\"></sup>be courageous and act.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then David gave to his son Solomon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11155R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11155R\"></sup>the plan of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11155S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11155S\"></sup>the porch <i>of the temple</i>, its buildings, its storehouses, its upper rooms, its inner rooms and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11155T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11155T\"></sup>the room for the mercy seat;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and the plan of all that he had in mind, for the courts of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and for all the surrounding rooms, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11156U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11156U\"></sup>the storehouses of the house of God and for the storehouses of the dedicated things;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>also for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11157V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11157V\"></sup>the divisions of the priests and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11157W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11157W\"></sup>the Levites and for all the work of the service of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and for all the utensils of service in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>for the golden <i>utensils</i>, the weight of gold for all utensils for every kind of service; for the silver utensils, the weight <i>of silver</i> for all utensils for every kind of service;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and the weight <i>of gold</i> for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11159X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11159X\"></sup>golden lampstands and their golden lamps, with the weight of each lampstand and its lamps; and <i>the weight of silver</i> for the silver lampstands, with the weight of each lampstand and its lamps according to the use of each lampstand;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and the gold by weight for the tables of showbread, for each table; and silver for the silver tables;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and the forks, the basins, and the pitchers of pure gold; and for the golden bowls with the weight for each bowl; and for the silver bowls with the weight for each bowl;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11162Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11162Y\"></sup>the altar of incense refined gold by weight; and gold for the model of the chariot, <i>even</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11162Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11162Z\"></sup>the cherubim that spread out <i>their wings</i> and covered the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“All <i>this</i>,” <i>said David</i>, “the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made me understand in writing by His hand upon me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11163AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11163AA\"></sup>all the details of this pattern.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then David said to his son Solomon, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11164AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11164AB\"></sup>Be strong and courageous, and act; do not fear nor be dismayed, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, my God, is with you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11164AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11164AC\"></sup>He will not fail you nor forsake you until all the work for the service of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is finished.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Now behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11165AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11165AD\"></sup><i>there are</i> the divisions of the priests and the Levites for all the service of the house of God, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11165AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11165AE\"></sup>every willing man of any skill will be with you in all the work for all kinds of service. The officials also and all the people will be entirely at your command.”"
		},
		"29": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">29 </span>Then King David said to the entire assembly, “My son Solomon, whom alone God has chosen, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11166A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11166A\"></sup>is still young and inexperienced and the work is great; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11166B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11166B\"></sup>the temple is not for man, but for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11167C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11167C\"></sup>with all my ability I have provided for the house of my God the gold for the <i>things of</i> gold, and the silver for the <i>things of</i> silver, and the bronze for the <i>things of</i> bronze, the iron for the <i>things of</i> iron, and wood for the <i>things of</i> wood, onyx stones and inlaid <i>stones</i>, stones of antimony and stones of various colors, and all kinds of precious stones and alabaster in abundance.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Moreover, in my delight in the house of my God, the treasure I have of gold and silver, I give to the house of my God, over and above all that I have already provided for the holy temple,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><i>namely</i>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11169D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11169D\"></sup>3,000 talents of gold, of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11169E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11169E\"></sup>the gold of Ophir, and 7,000 talents of refined silver, to overlay the walls of the buildings;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>of gold for the <i>things of</i> gold and of silver for the <i>things of</i> silver, that is, for all the work done by the craftsmen. Who then is willing to consecrate himself this day to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11171F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11171F\"></sup>the rulers of the fathers’ <i>households</i>, and the princes of the tribes of Israel, and the commanders of thousands and of hundreds, with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11171G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11171G\"></sup>the overseers over the king’s work, offered willingly;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and for the service for the house of God they gave 5,000 talents and 10,000 <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11172H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11172H\"></sup>darics of gold, and 10,000 talents of silver, and 18,000 talents of brass, and 100,000 talents of iron.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Whoever possessed <i>precious</i> stones gave them to the treasury of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, in care of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11173I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11173I\"></sup>Jehiel the Gershonite.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the people rejoiced because they had offered so willingly, for they made their offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11174J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11174J\"></sup>with a whole heart, and King David also rejoiced greatly.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So David blessed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the sight of all the assembly; and David said, “Blessed are You, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel our father, forever and ever.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11176K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11176K\"></sup>Yours, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, is the greatness and the power and the glory and the victory and the majesty, indeed everything that is in the heavens and the earth; Yours is the dominion, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and You exalt Yourself as head over all.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11177L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11177L\"></sup>Both riches and honor <i>come</i> from You, and You rule over all, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11177M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11177M\"></sup>in Your hand is power and might; and it lies in Your hand to make great and to strengthen everyone.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now therefore, our God, we thank You, and praise Your glorious name.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“But who am I and who are my people that we should be able to offer as generously as this? For all things come from You, and from Your hand we have given You.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11180N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11180N\"></sup>we are sojourners before You, and tenants, as all our fathers were; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11180O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11180O\"></sup>our days on the earth are like a shadow, and there is no hope.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, all this abundance that we have provided to build You a house for Your holy name, it is from Your hand, and all is Yours.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Since I know, O my God, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11182P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11182P\"></sup>You try the heart and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11182Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11182Q\"></sup>delight in uprightness, I, in the integrity of my heart, have willingly offered all these <i>things</i>; so now with joy I have seen Your people, who are present here, make <i>their</i> offerings willingly to You.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Abraham, Isaac and Israel, our fathers, preserve this forever in the intentions of the heart of Your people, and direct their heart to You;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11184R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11184R\"></sup>give to my son Solomon a perfect heart to keep Your commandments, Your testimonies and Your statutes, and to do <i>them</i> all, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11184S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11184S\"></sup>to build the temple, for which I have made provision.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then David said to all the assembly, “Now bless the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.” And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11185T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11185T\"></sup>all the assembly blessed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11185U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11185U\"></sup>bowed low and did homage to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and to the king.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>On the next day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11186V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11186V\"></sup>they made sacrifices to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and offered burnt offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, 1,000 bulls, 1,000 rams <i>and</i> 1,000 lambs, with their drink offerings and sacrifices in abundance for all Israel.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So they ate and drank that day before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with great gladness.And they made Solomon the son of David king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11187W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11187W\"></sup>a second time, and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11187X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11187X\"></sup>anointed <i>him</i> as ruler for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and Zadok as priest.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11188Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11188Y\"></sup>Solomon sat on the throne of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as king instead of David his father; and he prospered, and all Israel obeyed him.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>All the officials, the mighty men, and also all the sons of King David pledged allegiance to King Solomon.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11190Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11190Z\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> highly exalted Solomon in the sight of all Israel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11190AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11190AA\"></sup>bestowed on him royal majesty which had not been on any king before him in Israel.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11191AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11191AB\"></sup>David the son of Jesse reigned over all Israel.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11192AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11192AC\"></sup>The period which he reigned over Israel <i>was</i> forty years; he reigned in Hebron seven years and in Jerusalem thirty-three <i>years</i>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then he died in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11193AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11193AD\"></sup>a ripe old age, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11193AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11193AE\"></sup>full of days, riches and honor; and his son Solomon reigned in his place.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Now the acts of King David, from first to last, are written in the chronicles of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11194AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11194AF\"></sup>Samuel the seer, in the chronicles of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11194AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11194AG\"></sup>Nathan the prophet and in the chronicles of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11194AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11194AH\"></sup>Gad the seer,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>with all his reign, his power, and the circumstances which came on him, on Israel, and on all the kingdoms of the lands."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;